title: hollandaise sauce
directions: In small saucepan, stir together real mayonnaise, milk, salt and pepper.
Stir in lemon rind, lemon juice and food coloring. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, about 4 minutes
or until heated.
Serve over hot, cooked asparagus.
Makes 4 servings.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients; pat into pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients, except nuts.
Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350°.
Cool and cut.

title: garlic cheese french bread
directions: Grate cheddar cheese into large bowl.
Mash room temperature butter into cheese.

Add parsley and lemon juice and garlic. Cheese mixture should be spreadable consistency, (if cheese or butter is too cold, it won't mix together as well, so you may warm mixture in microwave to spreadable consistency).

title: yogurt sundae
directions: Reserve some fruit for garnish (if desired).
Puree remainder in blender.
Combine pureed fruit, sugar, yogurt and extract. Spoon into individual dessert dishes.
Garnish and serve.
Yield: 3 to 4 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix juice of 2 cans oranges, 1 can plus 3 tablespoons pineapple juice and vanilla pudding.
Cook until thickened.
Cool.
Mix all fruits and walnuts together and fold in pudding mixture.

title: fried okra
directions: Cut tender, young okra into 1 inch rounds and season with creole seasoning.
In a small mixing bowl, beat egg and add milk. Dip okra in mixture and roll in seasoned cornmeal.
Fry in 360° oil until crisp and brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: carrot pie
directions: Drain the carrots and put through sieve.
There should be a generous cup.
Combine with sugar, salt and spice.
Add beaten eggs, milk and butter.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: ketchup
directions: Drain water off tomato juice after setting for 2 hours, then put juice through blender.
Mix all with a little cold water and add to juice.
Boil for 3 to 3 1/2 hours, then thicken with Clear Jell; bottle and seal.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 3 items and cook 7 minutes.
Add 1 heaping cup peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs in mixing bowl until light.
Melt butter and add to eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and blend in.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 345° for 30 to 45 minutes until firm.

title: hanky pankies
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage together.
Drain well.
Add seasonings.
Cut cheese into cubes and stir until well melted. Spread mixture on bread.
Broil until hot and bubbly.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Put all ingredients as listed (except evaporated milk) in pan. Pour evaporated milk over all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brandied fruit cake
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar.
Beat in eggs, flour and spices.
Batter will be thick.
Add fruit and some juice.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into a greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or at 350° for 15 minutes; then turn down to 300° for remaining 45 minutes.

title: fiesta corn salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients and chill.
Good salad for any meal and it is so good and looks so pretty.

title: meatballs with rice
directions: Combine together ground beef, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, onion, milk and rice.
Form into 9 balls and put into a 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix together tomato soup, brown sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: tomato florentine soup
directions: Simmer the first 6 ingredients over low heat until tender, about 45 minutes. Add the tomato juice, chicken bouillon or base and 1/2 can of water. Salt, pepper and Lawry's to taste. Add the macaroni. Heat until hot. May add hamburger to it.

title: biroux
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain. Add spices and mix well. Add cabbage and onion. Cook 15 minutes. May need to add a little water. Roll thawed rolls on floured board to 6-inch square. Put spoon of cheese, then 1/2 cup of hamburger. Gather up 3 sides, then remaining side and pinch together. Lay pinched side down on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until brown.

title: chewy chocolate nuggets
directions: Blend sugar, margarine and chocolate in a large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, until well blended.
Mix in vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to chocolate mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Cover and chill 2 hours or overnight.

title: oatmeal mini pancakes with apple-pear sauce
directions: In large bowl, stir together first 7 ingredients.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Stir together eggs, milk and oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Pour 2 tablespoons batter for each pancake onto hot, lightly greased griddle or skillet.
Cook pancakes until tops are covered with bubbles and edges look cooked; flip.
Serve with apple-pear sauce.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Mix soup, water, tapioca, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over cut up meat and vegetables.
Cover and bake at 275° for 5 hours.
Do not raise lid or open oven door while cooking.

title: sherry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix 5 minutes.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Prick with a fork and drizzle with frosting (2 cup powdered sugar and 1/4 cup sherry wine).

title: poor man's cake
directions: Sift sugar, flour, soda, cocoa and salt in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake in 300° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix in order as listed.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: mystery rolls
directions: Do not use salad dressing.
Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix.
Pour batter into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 muffins.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all together.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup.

title: bread loaf bake
directions: Brown hamburger. Drain and add remaining ingredients. Roll out dough and place on 9 X 13 pan. Place hamburger mixture in middle and pull dough over top. Butter the top and sprinkle with parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for up to 30 minutes.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients. Take out 9 slices of dried beef. Chip up the rest real fine and mix into cheeses.
On wax paper, lay the chipped beef out.
Place the cheese mixture in the middle and shape into a long roll.
Fold the chipped beef over cream cheese. Wrap in wax paper and chill. Slice into rounds.

title: zesty beef-biscuit casserole
directions: Crumble beef into skillet.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook on medium until meat loses red color.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt.
Simmer mixture while preparing dough.

title: apricot fried pies
directions: Combine shortening and flour with a pastry blender.
Add water a little at a time, tossing with a fork to mix.
Form a ball; cover and set aside.
Dice apricots.
Cover with water in a heavy saucepan; cover and simmer until apricots are tender.
Uncover and continue cooking until all of the water is cooked out.
Add sugar and spice to the apricots, cooking until sugar dissolves.
Cool. Roll out dough on floured surface and cut into 8 (6-inch) circles. Place 1/4 cup filling on each; fold in half and moisten edges with a little water to seal. Crimp edges with a fork.
Heat oil to 375° and deep fry pies about 3 minutes until golden brown.
Drain and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Saute lightly in covered pan with 2 to 3 tablespoons of butter for 10 minutes the zucchini and garlic.
Place in blender with chicken broth, condensed milk or cream and curry powder.
Heat gently and enjoy! Yields approximately 4 servings.

title: french meat pie
directions: Grind beef, pork and onion and mix well.
Add water and seasoning.
Cook and stir until all red color disappears from meat. Remove from heat and cool.
Add cracker crumbs to thicken.
Line 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Fill with meat mixture.
Cover with top crust.
Cut slashes and flute edges.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: easy oven stew
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coat meat in flour and salt.
Brown in melted shortening in Dutch oven.
Add soup and 2 1/2 cups water. Add basil and mix well.
Bring to boil; cover and bake in oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables and wine.
Cover and bake an additional hour or until vegetables are tender, adding more wine or water as necessary.
Liquid should be on the thick side.

title: georgia delight
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: glazed meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, eggs, catsup, horseradish (if using) and water in large bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into a loaf on a well-greased jelly roll pan.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Baste with half the Glaze.
Continue baking for 30 minutes longer.
Dilute remaining Glaze with 1/4 cup water.
Pour over loaf for a nice gravy.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and garlic in margarine. Combine mushroom soup, chicken and milk.
Pour into 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice; do not overcook.
In a mixing bowl, add sugar, butter flavor and nutmeg.
Stir well; add raisins.
Put into a well-buttered pan.
Bake in 325° oven for about 35 minutes or until done.

title: herb dip
directions: Mix and chill for 2 hours.
Use with any raw vegetable, as desired.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Soften butter; whip and then blend in jam and lemon juice. Place in a covered container and refrigerate until ready to use. Butter may be frozen and later used for spread on toast, waffles or quick breads.

title: sea king dinner
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add the chopped green pepper, onion and celery; saute until tender.
Stir in the flour, paprika, cayenne pepper, garlic salt and salt.
Add the milk.
Cook, stirring until thick.
Stir in the frozen soup.

title: twinkie frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour until thick; cool. Beat remaining ingredients 4 minutes. Add flour mixture; beat another 4 minutes. Spread on cake or layered cake.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Let set until cool and starts to jell, then whip the evaporated milk and combine these 2 together, then add pineapple, cottage cheese, walnuts and mayonnaise.
Stir all together and chill.
Decorate with cherries.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: In a small bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened milk.
Then peanut butter until smooth.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream butter or margarine.
Add grated cheese, flour and baking powder; mix thoroughly.
Fold in Rice Krispies (mixture will be stiff).
Form small balls; place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork tines.
Sprinkle wafers with paprika before baking. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sausage-cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage in serving pieces; place in casserole dish.
Cover bottom of dish with water.
Cut sausage into 2-inch pieces and place on top of cabbage.
Cook until cabbage is tender, approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add oatmeal to boiling water.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Cream butter, white sugar, brown sugar and eggs until sugars dissolve. Add vanilla, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well; add oatmeal.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: venison steak
directions: Slice the steak thin; mix flour, salt and pepper in a paper bag.
Shake the steak in the bag until the meat is coated good. Put the shortening in a hot frying pan and put the meat in.
Brown and turn and cook until the blood is all gone and golden brown.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Drain spinach well and squeeze.
Add eggs, cottage cheese, Old English cheese and flour.
Place in casserole.
Slice margarine and place on top.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions and drain.
Stir in cheese mix, sour cream
and milk.
Pour in slightly greased baking dish and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Sprinkle paprika on top and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sandwich filling
directions: Add chili sauce to ground up mixture, along with relish and mayonnaise.
Put in wiener bun and wrap in foil and store in crisper.
Heat in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
They keep well.

title: dirt pie
directions: Crush the Oreo cookies.
Reserve 1/4 cup.
Mix 1/2 cup melted margarine with the Oreos.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the milk with the pudding.
In a separate bowl, mix the cream cheese with the powdered sugar. Combine the two mixtures well. Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture over crumbs.
Sprinkle with reserved 1/4 cup crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: funnel cakes(makes 6 large cakes)
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add the egg and milk and stir until well blended. Let the mixture stand for 15 minutes.

title: basic vegetable mixture
directions: Run vegetables through a meat grinder or blender.
(Makes 1 cup.)
You can double this recipe to suit your needs.

title: party cones
directions: In a bowl, mix peanuts or nuts, raisins, M&M's and cereal. Spoon mixture into ice cream cones to approximately 3/4 full. Place one cone at each party guest's place.

title: pork chops pacifica
directions: Season pork chops to taste with salt and pepper.
Brown well on both sides.
Put in a shallow baking dish.
Stir instant chicken broth into boiling water and pour mixture over chops.
Add rice, onions, tomato and green peppers.
Sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Cover tightly with lid or foil.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: summer squash or zucchini
directions: Mix together vegetables and tomatoes.
Crumble up crackers and mix with remaining ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into 2 1/2-inch cakes.
Chill, covered loosely, for 30 minutes.
In large skillet, melt 1 tablespoon butter over medium heat until foaming.
Cook crab cakes for 5 minutes on each side until golden brown.

title: meringue dessert
directions: Beat the whites as stiff as possible.
Add the sugar gradually, then in turn the salt, vanilla and vinegar.
Grease 2 pans with butter; pour in the mixture and bake in a moderate oven, about 45 minutes.
Cut in squares.
Cover 1/2 of the squares with whipped cream, with preserves or fruit on top.
This is filling, over which must be placed the other squares, which again have whipped cream heaped over them with a touch of preserves or fruit.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into bite size balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Makes about 40 balls.
Can be made ahead and frozen uncooked.

title: pickled peppers
directions: Bring to a boil and drop in mangos that have been quartered. When they lose color, put in hot jars.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar.
Let stand.
Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Chill, but do not congeal.
Add other ingredients.
Stir well and let set to congeal.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Prepare cornbread mix according to the directions on the package.
Pour melted butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine broccoli, cornbread, eggs, cottage cheese and onion.
Pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: twice baked potatoes with broccoli
directions: Pierce potato skin with a fork.
Bake potatoes at 450° for 45 minutes or until fork-tender.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut a thin slice off the top of each potato.
Carefully scoop out potato insides; reserve shells.

title: sara's hush puppies
directions: Blend
dry
ingredients together with fork.
Add enough water to
make
mixture
consistency
of sour cream.
Drop by scant teaspoonfuls into hot 375° fat.
Fry until golden brown (5 to 7 minutes).
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Cool.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together.
Serve with crackers.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter.
Pour it in casserole dish.
Put frozen country-style hash browns in over butter.
Mix in a bowl the cream of chicken soup, sour cream, shredded cheese and onion. Put the mixture in on top of the hash browns.
Put crushed cornflakes on top. Bake at 350°.

title: red pepper jelly
directions: Grind peppers and onion; strain.
Toss with 1 1/2 teaspoons salt.
Let this drain for 3 hours.
Squeeze dry with hands.
In large pot, combine vegetables with the remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, sugar, vinegar, lemon juice, cloves and red pepper flakes. Boil 10 minutes.
Add pectin and boil 1 minute.
Pour into scalded jars and top with melted wax.

title: layered salad
directions: Place the layers of salad in a straight sided salad bowl in the order in which they are listed.
On the top layer of lettuce, spread the mayonnaise 1/2-inch thick on top of the vegetables, sealing the vegetables.
Sprinkle with the sugar and cover with plastic wrap.
It must be sealed against air.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: main dish(my favorite recipe)
directions: Mix well and add tears of joy, sympathy and sorrow for others.
Flavor with little gifts of love.
Fold in 6 cups of prayer and faith.
Pour all into daily life.
Bake well with human kindness.
Serve with a large smile.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and process until smooth. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/4
c. Use instead of purchased can.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except dressing and margarine.
Put in casserole dish. Sprinkle Pepperidge Farm dressing mix lightly on top.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and pour over the top.
Bake at 350° until hot, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar.
Set aside.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add juice and chill until partially set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until set.

title: i can't believe it's cauliflower salad
directions: Combine bacon, lettuce, cauliflower and green onions. At serving time, mix together mayo and sugar and pour over lettuce; mix well and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: bread and butter pickle
directions: Wash
cucumbers and slice;
layer in pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup salt and set for 2 hours.
Place vinegar and spice mixture in boiler;
bring to a good boil.
Place cucumbers in mixture; spoon into jars and seal while hot.

title: bubble up pizza
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters with scissors. Mix in spaghetti sauce, cheese and toppings.
Save a little bit of the sauce and cheese for top. Put into 9 x 13 pan. Put on sauce and cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown shortening, onions and lean beef.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat for 1 hour.

title: mock souffle
directions: Butter a 17 x 12-inch pan.
Lay half of bread in pan.
Cover with half of Swiss, half of ham and half of American cheese. Repeat with remaining bread, Swiss, ham and American cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard and onions together; pour over top.
Cover with cornflake crumbs and lay bacon on top.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° or 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate fondue
directions: In fondue dish, melt the marshmallows and frosting on stove. At the table, set fondue dish on low and dip fruit with fondue fork into dip.
Enjoy.

title: banana muffins
directions: In a medium bowl, mash bananas (about 1 cup).
Stir in cereal. Stir in milk and set aside.
Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in egg.
Beat in bran cereal mixture.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to mixture.
Stir in raisins if desired.

title: pat's eggnog recipe
directions: Beat the egg yolks with electric mixer until thick and almost white. Continue beating and add in the granulated sugar, cognac and brandy.
Fold in 3 quarts heavy cream and 6 egg whites that were whipped until soft peaks formed.
In another bowl, beat 6 egg whites very stiff. Gradually add to it the powdered sugar, then fold this mixture into the eggnog.
In another bowl, whip 3 cups heavy cream until barely holds its shape.
Blend this mixture into the eggnog with a rubber spatula.
Let eggnog "rest" 12 to 14 hours before serving.

title: multi-nut brittle
directions: Generously butter a cookie sheet.
In a large saucepan over high heat, cook sugar, water and corn syrup until mixture reaches 280° on a candy thermometer.
Slowly add nuts and cook, stirring, until temperature reaches 300°.
Turn off heat.
Carefully stir in butter and vanilla until blended.
Add baking soda and stir vigorously but cautiously.
Pour mixture onto prepared cookie sheet and spread as thinly as possible with a wooden spoon.
Cool completely.
Break cooled candy into pieces.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: peanut butter-oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients; blend well. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press each with a fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 5 to 10 dozen cookies.

title: banana punch
directions: Let frozen juices thaw.
Bring water to boil.
Stir in sugar and let cool.
Add orange juice, pineapple juice, lemonade and bananas.
Let freeze.
Cut out any amount and pour ginger ail over and serve cold.

title: apricot salad
directions: Drain fruits, reserving syrup.
Cut apricots into small pieces.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add 1 1/2 cups fruit syrup; cool.
Add fruit, nuts and marshmallows.
Turn into oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Add flour, alternately with mixture.
Drop by spoonful into greased muffin tins.
Bake in 425° oven until golden brown.

title: peanut butter cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a double boiler; cook for 3 to 5 hours until solid.
Cool.
When cold this is ready for use.
It may be eaten like cheese, sliced and stewed with peas, made into hash with potatoes or as a sandwich filling.

title: pecan roast
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sweeten to taste.
Set in refrigerator overnight to set.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients in medium bowl by hand, not with a mixer.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350°
until the filling sets up.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Lay chicken breasts in bottom of casserole dish.
Place slice of cheese on top of each piece of chicken.
Mix one cup wine with cream of chicken soup in separate bowl to blend.
Pour over chicken in dish.
Crush crumbs of stuffing to smaller pieces and pour over chicken mixture.
(Be sure to mix herbs into crumbs before spreading.)
Bake in oven for 45 minutes.

title: quick nut bread
directions: Place chopped nut meats in boiling water for 2 minutes.
Drain well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine milk, egg and shortening with nut meats.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until lightly browned.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Sift together sugar and self-rising flour.
Mix in saucepan the margarine, cocoa and water.

Bring to rapid boil and pour over flour mixture, mixing well, then add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla. Mix and pour in an 11 x 16-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 400°. Make frosting while cake is baking.

title: cherry rice pudding
directions: In a large pot over medium heat, bring milk, rice, sugar, salt and ginger to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until rice is very tender, about 1 hour. In a small bowl, beat eggs slightly; stir in small amount of hot rice mixture.
Slowly pour egg mixture into rice mixture in pot, stirring rapidly to prevent lumps.
Over low heat, cook, stirring constantly, until rice mixture thickens, about 5 minutes.
Do not let pudding boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Transfer to a bowl; cover and chill 1 hour.

title: oreo pie
directions: Crumble 2 cups Oreo cookies (filling and all).
Mix in butter. Press into a 9-inch pie pan and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Let cool and add filling.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Bake at 350° about 14 minutes.

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef, celery and onions.
Add soups, noodles, mushrooms and water. Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle some noodles on top.

title: hot chicken sandwiches
directions: Mix together and fill hamburger buns.
Can wrap in foil and warm in oven for 15 minutes at 350° or warm in microwave carefully.

title: coconut cake(delicious)
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package in 2 layers. Completely cool; split each layer in half.

title: "fried" chicken(lo-cal, low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a rack with Pam and place on cookie sheet.
Mix crumbs and seasonings.
Coat chicken with yogurt. Press crumbs on chicken.
Bake 45 minutes until lightly browned and juices run clear.

title: won tons
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix hamburger and other ingredients over heat until well blended.
Use to fill won ton shell (directions on back of package).
Deep fry until browned.
Can be made ahead.
To reheat, bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Can use salsa for dipping.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 325° preheated oven in a 9 x 13-inch pan or round cake pan.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: apple bars
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and egg.
Add remaining ingredients, except apple.
Mix well.
Add apples last and stir in just enough to mix into dough.
Bake in greased 9-inch square pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a 9-inch tube pan. Blend butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat until frothy.
Add the almond extract.
In three additions, add the flour alternately with the orange juice.
Add the orange or lemon rind.
Beat egg whites until stiff and gently fold into the batter.
Bake for 50 minutes or until a cake tester comes out dry. Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn out on rack to finish cooling.

title: rum balls
directions: Put cookies and nut meats in blender or meat grinder.
Add remainder of ingredients in order given.
Knead into workable dough; shape into small balls and roll in confectioners sugar and refrigerate.
Let mellow for one day before using.

title: potato rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except eggs, well with 1 cup of the flour.
Add the eggs, then add the rest of the flour.
Put into a greased bowl and let rise to double size.
Push down and refrigerate overnight.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add Ro-Tel, seasoning, soup, Velveeta and rice.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: fast fudge
directions: Mix peanut butter and vanilla in bowl.
Mix sugar and milk in saucepan, let boil for 1 minute.
Pour sugar and milk mixture into bowl with peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Pour mixture into buttered plate.
Cut when cool.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Scald milk over low heat; gradually stir in corn meal.
Cook to consistency of mush, stirring often.
Add butter, baking powder, salt, sugar and egg yolks which have been beaten until light.
Cool slightly.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry. Fold into batter.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake in a slow oven (325°) for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve at once with plenty of butter or gravy.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cream cheese crepes
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Lay 1 tube of rolls flat in bottom for crust.
Combine sugar, cream cheese, egg yolk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Spread on layer of rolls.
Top with other tube of rolls.
Mix egg white, 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Spread on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° .

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine chocolate chips and milk in glass microwavable dish. Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Mix in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm. Cut into squares.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour over chicken wings in a roasting pan. Cook at 350° for 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours.
Turn wings several times. Can cook all, freeze half, then microwave.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and peanut butter.
Add flour and soda.
Add chocolate chips.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: bay scallops with almonds
directions: In a medium size saucepan, combine the wine and fish stock or clam juice.
Bring to a simmer over high heat, cooking until reduced to 1/2 cup, about 6 minutes.
Add the cream and cook until thickened to coat the back of a spoon, about 10 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Remove from heat.
In a large nonstick skillet, heat the butter over high heat.
Add the scallops and cook until browned and well-seared, about 2 minutes.
Stir scallops and finish cooking until slightly firm, about one minute, depending on the size.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Transfer to a colander to drain.
Add the scallops to the sauce, mixing to coat. Spoon the scallops into the center of the serving plates.
Top with chives and almonds.
Position the garnish chives into the top of the scallop mound and serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat, add next four ingredients and simmer.
Cook noodles.
Mix together cottage cheese, eggs, salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Place 1/2 noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, spread 1/2 cottage cheese mixture and 1/2 meat mixture.
Add 1/2 pound American cheese, sliced thin.
Repeat layers and cover with 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Serves 12.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Prepare sausage and drain. Separate rolls into 8 triangles. Place in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points to center. Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust. Seal perforations. Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes. Top with Cheddar cheese. In a bowl, beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle Parmesan over all.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: veal cutlets
directions: Use your favorite sauce.
Pour some in bottom of baking dish; add veal cutlets and
pour remainder of tomato sauce on top. Sprinkle with some	grated	cheese	and
about 1/2 pound Mozzarella cheese.	Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: crab cakes
directions: Use enough bread crumbs or cracker meal to be able to form cakes.
Use parsley and salt if desired.
Brown in oil until brown, turning once.

title: okra seafood gumbo
directions: Cook okra until there is no more slime (1 tablespoon of vinegar helps).
Add 1/2 cup roux.
Saute chopped vegetables and add to okra.
Add 2 to 3 quarts water and simmer for 1 or 2 hours.
Add salt, pepper and red pepper to taste.
Add seafood and cook 30 to 45 minutes more.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix
flour,
butter and chopped pecans.
Spread mixture evenly in
x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Let
cool. While
crust is cooling, mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and
Cool Whip.
Spread on top of cooled crust. Spread pie filling on top of mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Blend cornstarch and sugar; add water and cook for 15 minutes, stirring constantly until thick.
Add lemon juice, rind and butter.

title: pa's mayonnaise cake
directions: Knead all ingredients by hand.
Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar; pat firmly on bottom of buttered 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt margarine, add onion, celery, and garlic. Saute until tender. Blend in flour, salt, pepper, paprika, chili powder and tabasco. Add tomatoes including liquid, simmer 10 minutes. Add shrimp, heat to cook shrimp and serve over rice.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Combine butter and Worcestershire sauce. Add chicken and toss to coat. In plastic bag, put crackers and cheese. Add chicken. Shake to coat. Put chicken in pan. Bake at 450° for 7 minutes.

title: butterscotch cream cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. On low speed, beat in water and pudding mix until smooth. Fold in half of the whipped topping and pour into crust. Chill 2 hours or until set. Garnish with remaining whipped topping and serve. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain all beans and mix with onion and bell pepper.
Mix vinegar, oil and sugar in blender and pour over beans.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place torn bread in a 9 x 13-inch buttered baking dish.
Brown and drain sausage.
Spoon over bread.
Sprinkle with the cheese. Beat together the eggs, milk and salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cheese rises to the top.
Can make the day before and refrigerate until time to bake.

title: red cabbage salad(servings: 4)
directions: Fry bacon in medium-size frypan until crisp.
Remove and reserve bacon.
Add sugar, vinegar and wine to bacon fat; stir and cook until sugar is dissolved.
Pour this hot mixture over the cabbage.
Toss with vegetable oil, salt, pepper and caraway seed. Sprinkle crumbled bacon over mixture.
Serve at room temperature.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Hollow out fresh pineapple and use for a bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients well.

title: honey peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together thoroughly.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Chill dough. Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on lightly greased cookie tin.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour; crisscross.
Bake until set but not hard at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: savory venison pot roast
directions: In large saucepot, brown roast on all sides in vegetable oil. After browning, drain fat. Add mushroom soup, onion soup mix and 1 cup water.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook until tender (depends on size of roast, about 3 to 3 1/2 hours).
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook about 45 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender. Remove roast and vegetables.
Stir together flour and remaining 1/4 cup water.
Gradually stir into soup mixture.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.

title: fruit salad
directions: Peel and chop apples.
Peel and slice banana.
Drain fruit cocktail.
Mix together.
Add marshmallows to taste.
Add Cool Whip to taste.
Stir well.
Everyone loves this, especially the kids.
Easy to make and quick!
Serves 4.

title: hot dog chili i
directions: Brown ground beef. Add onion, salt, pepper and chili powder. Add sugar, catsup, vinegar and water. Stir and simmer 20 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and lightly flour a 13 x 9 in pan.
Mix water, oil eggs, and cake mix.
Blend on low speed for 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 35 - 38 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into center of cake comes out clean.
While cake is still warm punch holes into cake with a straw or toothpick and pour milk over top of cake.
Melt icing for 45 seconds in microwave.
Stir and pour over the top of cake.
Slice and serve.

title: 6 weeks bran muffins no. 4(yields 24 servings)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and beat.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Alternate flour and buttermilk while beating.
Add cereal and mix well.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Test for doneness.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Pit, peel and mash avocados. Add lemon juice, salt and pepper. Set aside.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning. Set aside.

title: date bars
directions: Cut dates into small pieces.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat until light.
Add vanilla.
Gradually blend in dry ingredients.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Spread evenly in a greased and floured 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake in 375° oven about 30 minutes, until firm when touched lightly.
When cool, cut into bars.
These freeze well.

title: fried okra salad
directions: Dice okra and season with salt and pepper.
Dredge with 1/2 cornmeal and 1/2 flour.
Fry in hot oil until done.
Drain well on paper towel.
Toss in tomatoes and onion.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: tutti frutti cookies
directions: Melt shortening and cool.
Add molasses, sugar and egg.
Beat until well blended.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices together and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Finely chop the raisins, nuts and fruit.
Fold into batter.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto a baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Grease crock-pot.
Mix all ingredients (saving some of the cheese).
Pour into crock-pot.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Cook on low for 3 1/4 hours.
Do not stir.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water. Stir in rest of water, flour and sugar. Beat until smooth. Cover with thin cloth. Let stand at room temperature for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times a day. Cover and refrigerate until ready to use. To keep starter going, add 3/4 cup water, 3/4 cup flour and 1 teaspoon sugar to remaining starter after some is used. Let stand at room temperature until bubbly and well fermented, at least 1 day. Cover and refrigerate until ready to use again. If not used in 10 days, add 1 teaspoon sugar every 10 days.

title: cheese dip
directions: Coat pan with oil.
Add small portion of milk to pan.
Melt cheese gradually in milk.
Use a wooden spoon and stir gently.
Add green chilies and chopped tomatoes to mixture.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer potatoes in bottom of pan.
Layer broccoli on top of potatoes.
Stir soups.
Put raw chicken on top of broccoli, then put soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.
Put 4 slices of bread (buttered), broken up on top of casserole.
Turn broiler on; let bread crumbs get crunchy.

title: pecan french toast(easy overnight)
directions: Whisk together first 6 ingredients; slice bread in 1-inch pieces and lay them in a single layer, close together in oven-proof casserole dish.
(I use 9 1/2 x 13 1/2 x 2-inch.)
Pour milk mixture over; cover with plastic; refrigerate overnight.
In morning, allow to stand 15 minutes at room temperature.

title: iced tea soda
directions: Blend tea and corn syrup; fill a tall glass half full with mixture.
Add a scoop of ice cream, then fill the glass to the top with carbonated water.
Serves 8.

title: dixie green bean salad
directions: In a medium bowl, combine green beans, chickpeas, red pepper slices and onion.
In a small bowl or cup, combine oil, vinegar, mustard, Accent, sugar, salt, mint and pepper; mix well.
Pour over vegetables and toss lightly.
Cover.
Chill 1 hour before serving.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cornmeal pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into two unbaked crusts. Bake at 375° until firm and lightly browned.

title: herb dumplings
directions: Mix flour with suet or margarine, herbs and seasoning.
Add sufficient cold water to make a stiff dough.
Roll into balls. Cook at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 8 small dumplings. Dumplings are great with corned beef and cabbage.

title: fried rice
directions: Mix chicken, soy sauce, sesame oil and cornstarch in small bowl.
In another bowl, place peas and warm water to thaw peas slightly.
In a wok or skillet, heat a couple of tablespoons of oil.
To hot oil, add onion and garlic; cook until tender.
Remove from wok.
Cook meat mixture quickly on high heat; remove.
Add more oil to wok, if necessary.
Add cooked rice, scrambled eggs, onion, garlic and meat to wok.
Cook through.
Add soy sauce and red pepper to taste.

title: cheesecake
directions: Combine sugar and cream cheese.
Mix ingredients and pour into spring pan that has been buttered and dusted with graham cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Mix 1/2 pint sour cream and 2 tablespoons of sugar; pour over cheesecake and bake 5 minutes at 415°.
Chill.
Top with blueberries, strawberries, cherries or serve plain.

title: diabetic barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Add shortening and blend into dry ingredients until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine baking soda and buttermilk and stir into flour mixture.
Stir in dissolved yeast and mix well.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight or at least several hours.

title: herbed mushroom quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sprinkle cheese and mushrooms in pie crust.
In covered blender container on high speed, blend cottage cheese and remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour mixture into crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Turn oven to 325° and bake 35 minutes longer or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: 1-2-3-4 delight
directions: Melt butter and add flour.
Mix in 1/2 cup nuts for crust. Spread that in a 9-inch square cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°, then chill.

title: mussels with linguini
directions: Sort, scrub and rinse mussels.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Pat chicken dry and put into greased baking dish.

title: wet coconut cake
directions: Make cake mix as directed on the box.
Then add 1 more egg and the packet of Dream Whip.
Then bake cake as directed on box for two 9-inch cake pans.
When cake is done, let cool thoroughly. Then split each layer making a total of 4 layers.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes after cooking.
Add onion, sour cream and butter.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese. Refrigerate overnight, then bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done in the middle.
Makes 3 small loaves.

title: oriental fresh tomato and cucumber salad
directions: Tomatoes should be fully ripe and at room temperature.
Core and dice the tomatoes to make about 2 cups.
Place in medium bowl. Peel and halve cucumber lengthwise; seed and slice (makes about 3/4 cup).
Add cucumbers and scallions to tomatoes.
Toss gently. In a small bowl, combine sesame oil, soy sauce, red pepper and sugar.
Pour over tomato mixture; toss.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Makes three cups.

title: holiday stuffing
directions: Double recipe for a large turkey.

title: springeler's
directions: Beat eggs 15 to 20 minutes (should peak).
After beating eggs, blend all ingredients.
Refrigerate dough for 2 hours.

title: pear salad
directions: Heat juice and melt cream cheese; dissolve jello.
After this thickens, add mixed ingredients and cool a little before adding whipped cream.
Pineapple cubes may also be added.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into cakes.
Fry in vegetable oil approximately 6 minutes per side.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Boil chicken and pick off bone.
Cook rice according to directions, about 25 minutes.
Add cheese to rice while hot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in 9 x 13-inch pan and 8 x 8-inch square pan.
This can be made and refrigerated ahead of time.

title: pancakes
directions: Put in bowl.
Stir it up for 15 minutes.
Put it in pan. Watch it, when it is done on the other side you flip it.
You know it is done when it is brown (10 minutes).
Put it on plate and eat it.

title: decadent fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in large bowl.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with flour.
Add 1 cup mini morsels, melted chocolate, chocolate syrup and vanilla.
Spoon into a heavily greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 25 to 35 minutes.
Invert immediately onto cake plate and cool completely.
Frost.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together:
flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Set aside.

title: irene kehlor smith's sugared nuts
directions: Cook all ingredients (except nuts) until soft ball stage (240° on a candy thermometer).
Remove from heat; stir in nut meats. Pour onto waxed paper.
Separate nut halves.
Cool.

title: easy casserole
directions: Press 1 pound ground beef into an 8-inch square pan.
Salt and sprinkle with chopped onion to taste.
Pour over 1 undiluted can of cream of chicken or cream of celery soup.
Sprinkle 1 small can of drained peas over soup and top with frozen Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: swiss chard with tomatoes
directions: Trim coarse leaves and thick center ribs from chard.
Cut tender stems and leaves into 1/2-inch slices.
In a large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil.
Add bread crumbs, stirring often.
Cook until bread crumbs are crisp and golden.
Remove from skillet and set aside.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients lightly.
Pour into buttered casserole. Blend stuffing mix and softened margarine.
Spread on carrot mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple-lime punch
directions: Have all ingredients chilled.
Mix pineapple juice and soda in punch bowl.
Spoon in 1 pint of sherbet.
Just before serving, spoon in the second pint of sherbet.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until done.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla, beating until well blended.
Stir in nuts. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Immediately after removing from oven, pour the bag of marshmallows over cake; mash down.

title: almond pastry
directions: Cut 1/2 cup margarine into 1 cup flour.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of water.
Divide in half. Pat into strips on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Whip cream until thickened slightly. Quarter marshmallows. Cut cherries in half. Combine all ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and Crisco until like coarse crumbs.
Add water and mix well.
Roll out on lightly floured surface.
Makes one (9-inch) crust.
Bake at 425° until brown or use as unbaked pie shell.

title: dutch blueberry and cream pie
directions: Fill pie shell with blueberries.
Combine other ingredients and pour over berries.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut jelly bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix well. Stir in oats and nuts.
Press half of mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with jelly.
Cover with remaining crumb mixture. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Combine carrots, sugar, raisins, pineapple and mayonnaise. Mix well and chill.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook rice until tender, lightly brown meat, onions, garlic salt and peppers.
Mix with rice and 1 can tomato sauce.
Line a greased casserole with about half of the cabbage.
Spread meat mixture over this and cover with remaining cabbage.
Pour remaining can of tomato sauce over top.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water to boil; add oil.
Take off stove.
Add flour. Mix well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly browned at 325°.

title: mexican flan
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Caramelize 3 Tbsp. sugar in bottom of double boiler.
Add mixture to caramelized sugar and cook about 1 hour covered with lid.
Refrigerate to cool completely. Invert onto dish and serve cold.

title: boiled bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon slowly.
In a saucepan put sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Mix thoroughly.
Add beaten egg, vinegar, water, bacon and fat.
This is a dressing to use on dandelions, endive and lettuce.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in a small saucepan. Stir in cocoa.
Add baking powder, salt and add flour 1/4 cup at a time. Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake in preheated oven for 15 or 20 minutes or until done.

title: beef and onion casserole
directions: Brown hamburger. Drain and add tomato sauce, water and soup mix. Simmer 5 to 8 minutes. Cook macaroni and add.
Put in casserole dish and top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.
(Illinois.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix margarine with stuffing mix.
Place half of mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer chicken, onion and soups.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Pour chicken broth on top.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 2 tablespoons cocoa, milk, melted margarine and vanilla together in 9-inch square pan.
Spread evenly.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa and sprinkle over batter.
Pour water over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy and quick dessert
directions: *Or use graham cracker crust.

title: foil pot roast
directions: Place roast on large square of double-thick, heavy-duty foil. Lightly oil inner cooking square.
Season with salt and pepper and cover with soup.
Seal package and place on medium hot coals for about 3 hours.
Turn every 30 minutes.
After 2 hours of cooking, open package and check for doneness.
Rewrap and continue cooking until meat is tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together beans, soup, milk, pepper and 1/2 can of onions. Put in a casserole dish.
Cook on 350° for 25 minutes.
Pour the rest of the onions on top.
Cook 5 more minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into slices.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Put flour into a bowl.
Coat tomatoes with flour, a few at a time. Cook in hot oil until done.
(Cook on medium heat; don't overstir.)

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa; gradually stir in milk.
Add next 3 ingredients; mix well.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes without stirring. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Serve warm over vanilla ice cream.
Yields 1 cup.

title: mint brownies
directions: Use 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Best if made a day ahead.

title: brat salad
directions: Deep fry flour tortillas in shape of bowl. After cooled, put in lettuce, chicken breast, mandarin oranges, chopped tomatoes, pineapple chunks, coconut and English walnuts. Add dressing.

title: pumpkin oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients, cream oleo, sugar, add egg, vanilla.
Add all to dry ingredients.
Then add pumpkin and chocolate chips. Drop by spoonfuls.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 20 minutes.

title: bacon corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
In medium bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients, beating by hand just until smooth.
Sprinkle the batter with crumbled bacon before baking. Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 425° for 18 to 22 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 9 servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix butter, sugar and egg until light and fluffy.
Stir flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Roll dough into floured hands to desired size of pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook potatoes and onions in water until tender.
Add milk. Cook bacon until crisp.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir into the milk mixture.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add corn and reheat.

title: ham bites
directions: Lay out 4 slices bread; top with cheese and ham.
Repeat cheese and bread.
Cut into quarters.
Mix eggs and milk; add salt to taste.
Turn bread pieces in egg mixture, then in bread crumbs. Fry in hot fat until golden brown.
Serve hot.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant; cube into 1-inch cubes and boil in salted water until tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Heat the butter in a large pan.
Add the chopped onion; saute until golden and tender. (A diced green pepper may be added.) Add the tomato paste, the juice and the seasonings; bring to the boil, then remove from the heat.
Add the cooked eggplant and the bread crumbs; toss lightly until well mixed.
Turn into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with 1/4 cup buttered crumbs.
Heat at 350° until hot and bubbling.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat with mixer.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan as soon as you can handle.

title: cocktail bagels
directions: Combine ham, cheese, olives, onions, pepper and celery. Combine oil and tomato sauce; mix with other ingredients.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator to blend flavors.
Split bagels. Place 2 teaspoons mixture on each half and broil until bubbly. Make 40 pieces.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Blend sausage and cheese.
Work in Bisquick.
Form into balls. Bake at 425° until golden brown.
These keep well and can be frozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ground sirloin, bread crumbs, slightly beaten egg, tomatoes, olives, onion and other ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes.

title: polish chop suey
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients.
Cook noodles and mix everything together in a big roasting pan.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: pigs in blanket
directions: Beat brown sugar and eggs until thick.
Add cream of tartar, then butter, flour and soda to make a rich dough.
Roll out dough and cut into size of silver dollar.
Put 1 date in each and pinch up edges.
Bake on cookie sheets for 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 48.

title: impossible pie
directions: Method:
Preheat oven to 400°.
Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend well.
Pour into buttered deep 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until set.
Cool before serving. (Tastes like coconut custard pie.)

title: marinated catfish
directions: Mix oil, lemon and Worcestershire sauce in cooking pan. Place catfish in pan and coat with mixture.
Let marinate (best if overnight).
Cook at 350 degrees until flaky, coating with mixture while cooking on both sides.
Can also saute in pan on top
of stove.

title: crabby things
directions: Soften margarine and cheese in microwave. Add mayonnaise, garlic salt and crab. Spread on English muffins and place on cookie sheet. At this point, put them in the freezer for about 15 minutes before cutting into quarters, using a pizza cutter. Broil until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: holiday appetizer
directions: Cut bacon in half.
Wrap each water chestnut with half slice bacon; secure with toothpick.
Place in large skillet.
Mix catsup and brown sugar; add to skillet and stir to coat water chestnuts. Bring to boil, reduce heat to low and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Tilt pan to drain off bacon grease (I use a turkey baster).
Remove to serving platter; serve warm.
Bet you can't eat just one!

title: zesty snack mix
directions: Melt butter in microwave; add seasonings and stir until blended.
Pour half of butter mixture into large roasting pan.
Add cereals, nuts and pretzels; stir until coated.
Add remaining butter mixture and stir again until all pieces are coated.
Bake at 250 degrees for 1 hour.
Stir frequently to ensure that all pieces are baked.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Stir in airtight container.
Yield:
12 cups.

title: no bake peanut butter cup bars
directions: Mix together butter, crumbs, 1 cup peanut butter and powder ed sugar.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt 2 cups chocolate chips and 1 cup peanut butter; spread on crumb mixture.
Keep in refrigerator.
Cut into squares.
Butterscotch chips may also be used.

title: venison chateaubriand
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove all fat on venison.
Melt butter (save 2 tablespoons) and add garlic powder and celery salt.
Put venison in oblong pan and pour melted butter, seasonings and Worcestershire sauce over meat.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Turn while cooking.
While venison is baking, place reserved butter in large skillet.
Add cream cheese and mash with large spoon over medium heat for 20 minutes or until mixture becomes a thick gravy.
Add wine and cook another 10 minutes.
Carefully watch gravy to prevent burning!
Remove tenderloin and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Pour juices from venison into gravy and mix. Add venison to gravy and cook 5 more minutes.

title: cashew chicken stir-fry
directions: In wok or large frying pan, heat olive oil.
Add chicken and stir-fry over high heat until cooked.
Remove chicken; drain and set aside.

title: skip and go nakeds
directions: Mix and serve over ice.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: winter fruit pizza(very festive!)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice cookie dough as directed.
Arrange slices in bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Press dough evenly into pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: blender chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put liquid in blender first and then dry ingredients.
Mix well in blender.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven while center of pie is still shaky. Makes 2 deep dish pies.

title: meat-vegetable-potato casserole
directions: Simmer beef, onion and pepper in frying pan until thoroughly cooked.
Remove to casserole.
Add a layer of corn.
Cook potatoes and mash until creamy.
Spread over corn.
Add 3 squares of butter and a dash of paprika.
Place in oven at 350° for 15 minutes until heated thoroughly.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: In a food processor fitted with the steel blade, process all ingredients until blended.
Spoon into jars.
Cover and refrigerate until needed.
This recipe keeps indefinitely.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs and banana.
Add dry ingredients alternately with liquid.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan or 2 small 1 pound loaf pans, well-greased, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swedish slaw
directions: Bring first five ingredients to a boil.
Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl and pour boiling mixture over top.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well and add zucchini.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Grease pans.
Makes 3 small loaves.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Stir in salad dressing, mustard and honey together until well blended.
Place chicken on grill.
Brush with half of sauce. Grill 8 to 10 minutes; turn and brush with remaining sauce.
Grill 8 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: escalloped celery
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Put a layer of celery in dish.
Then sprinkle with crackers, chives and parsley.
Repeat layering until all celery and crackers are used. Heat milk and pour over contents of dish. Milk should cover.
If not, add more milk.
Dot with butter.
Dust with paprika. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until celery is cooked and milk absorbed.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Boil 3 cups water and baking soda.
Mix the warm water, brown sugar and yeast.
Set aside for 5 minutes.
Add the flour.
Stir until dough is not sticky.
Flatten onto floured surface; knead until elastic.
Form into pretzel shape.
Drop into boiling water for about 5 seconds.
Put on greased pan; sprinkle with salt. Bake at 475° for 8 minutes.

title: marinated pork tenderloin
directions: Slice tenderloins into 3/4-inch medallions. Combine remaining ingredients and process in food processor or blender until well mixed. Pour over meat and marinate for 1 hour or overnight. Grill over hot coals 20 to 30 minutes. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: different turkey casserole
directions: Arrange turkey in large baking dish. Melt butter; saute crumbs, celery and onion. Add salt, baking powder, pepper and poultry seasoning. Beat egg and combine with broth or milk. Add to crumbs. Pour over turkey; spread soup over top. Sprinkle with additional buttered bread crumbs. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serves 10 to 12.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Slowly cook beef and onion together.
Cook vegetables 10 to 12 minutes, then drain.
Mix altogether in pan and simmer together for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Dot top with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake for about 20 minutes at 325°.

title: lazy maple crescent pull apart rolls
directions: Heat oven to 375° and use 8 or 9-inch cake pan, ungreased. Combine brown sugar and syrup and oleo.
Place in oven 3 to 4 minutes or until oleo melts.
Blend well; sprinkle with nuts. Remove dough; do not unroll.
Cut roll into six slices.
In small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon, dip both sides of rolls in mixture.
Arrange in pan and sprinkle with remaining sugar mixture.
Bake at 375° for 17 to 23 minutes until brown.
Cool one minute, inverting onto serving platter.

title: banana split cake
directions: Place first 2 ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat next 3 ingredients for 15 minutes. Spread over graham cracker crumbs. Slice bananas and put over top of sugar mixture. Layer pineapple, whipped cream, cherries and nuts.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown 3 cloves of garlic in oil.
Remove garlic when brown. Simmer 1/2 hour with tomatoes, chili powder and salt.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Dip tortillas in tomato mixture until soft and pliable.
Fill each tortilla with beans, onions, meat and cheese.
Roll up and place in baking dish; pour a little sauce on bottom of baking dish.
When all tortillas are stuffed, pour remaining sauce over all and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Place in 400° oven until cheese is melted.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In frypan, cook onions, garlic and pepper until tender, not brown.
Skin chicken and add to pan.
Add the rest of ingredients; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Take out chicken and remove meat; return meat to pan and cover.
Cook 25 minutes still on simmer. Serve over rice or linguine.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Sift together dry ingredients; combine with zucchini mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.
(You may substitute 1/2 cup coarse bran for 1/2 cup of flour).

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, pepper and nutmeg. Add to beaten eggs, then stir in corn and milk. Pour into well buttered baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: cheddar beef goulash
directions: In skillet, brown beef in margarine.
Add onion.
Cook until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Stir in mushrooms and tomato sauce.
Simmer mixture 5 minutes.
Add noodles and green beans.
Toss lightly, but well.
Pour into greased shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly or lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: penny casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Layer bottom of casserole dish with 1/2 of beef.
Then layer onions, carrots and potatoes.
Add rest of beef and top with mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until desired tenderness.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop the artichoke hearts, combine with other ingredients. Blend until smooth.
Bake in 350° oven until warm and browned on top.
Serve with bread or crackers.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over crust and seal around top edge.
Mix together Jell-O and hot water.
Add frozen raspberries.
Pour onto cheese layer and chill.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Sprinkle inside of chicken pieces with salt. Combine egg, stuffing, 1/2 can of soup and next 5 ingredients. Top each breast with stuffing and skewer closed. Place in shallow casserole. Brush frequently with basting sauce made of remaining soup and last 5 ingredients. (Note: 1/4 teaspoon salt is in first 5 ingredients also in last 5 ingredients.) Bake at 375° until tender and brown.

title: raisin sauce (for ham)
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add raisins, vinegar and water.
Cook until it thickens some.

title: pork chop-apple bake
directions: Brown chops in 2 tablespoons butter.
Arrange chops, 1 layer deep, in a baking dish.
Sprinkle steak sauce over chops.
Mix apple, lemon peel, nutmeg, cinnamon, lemon juice and brown sugar. Spoon over chops; dot with remaining butter.
Add hot water. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer, or until chops are tender.

title: hominy
directions: On top of corn, sprinkle soda, then cover with boiling water. Cook until the eyes and hulls come off easily when put in cold water, usually about 1 1/2 hours (sometimes sooner).
Wash in cold water and rub between hands until eyes come off.
Wash in several kettles of water until water is clear.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt and cream of tartar in another large bowl.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in a small dish and set aside.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend all
ingredients,
cover	and
cool
for 2 hours. Slice top off
round
loaf
of bread.
Cut cubes of bread from center. Pile dip in bread shell and serve with bread cubes on side.

title: sweet potato biscuit with country ham
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add butter or margarine and sweet potatoes.
Add enough milk to make a dough that can be handled easily.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Pat or roll out and cut with medium biscuit cutter.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes until brown.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Slice.
Mix rest of ingredients. Layer sliced potatoes, alternating with layer of mixture.
Allow to marinate overnight.

title: six cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand for 2 or 3 hours before serving.
Garnish with red and green cherries for the holiday season or with unpeeled red chunks of apples for the Autumn.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed on box, making two layers. Cool.
Prepare pudding and chill.

title: copper pennies(marinated carrots)
directions: Cut carrots into thin slices.
Place in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain.
Chop green pepper small.
Thinly slice onions. Cut slices smaller or use very small onions.

title: linguine salad
directions: Break linguine into 3 or 4 pieces; cook and drain.
Chop fine tomatoes, cucumber, onion, green pepper and celery.
Mix with linguine, salad dressing and Salad Supreme.
Serve cold.
Even better the second day!

title: chicken breast and rice casserole
directions: Heat soups.
Add rice; pour over chicken in casserole.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Pour the liquid from the sweet potatoes into a saucepan.
Heat with water and sugar.
Add mashed sweet potatoes; add butter, cinnamon, ginger, pecans, pineapple and brown sugar.
Just bring to a boil; let cool.
Roll into balls and roll in coconut.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: rice and chicken almondine(low calorie)
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Cook onion until soft.
Add flour and heat until bubbly.
Remove from heat; add chicken broth, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in water.
Heat thoroughly; do not boil.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Turn into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cook at 375°
for 25 minutes or until well heated.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Sift powdered sugar.
Beat oleo with mixer.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat well.
Chop pecans until fine, but not ground up and stir into mixture.
Add coconut.
Place in refrigerator to chill. Roll into small balls. Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in top of double boiler.
Dip candy in chocolate.
Place on waxed paper to dry.
Store in airtight container.

title: cheese and onion potatoes
directions: In a skillet, melt butter or magarine over medium-high heat. Add potatoes, onion and pepper.
Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender, about 10 minutes. Uncover, cook until potatoes are browned, about 5 to 7 minutes. Top with cheese.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for several minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread the pineapple, juice included, in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Spoon the cherry filling on top and sprinkle the dry cake mix over this.
Spread the pecans over all and dot top with margarine. Do not stir any of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green beans and tomatoes
directions: Brown onion in hot oil.
Add tomatoes and herbs; cook about 15 minutes.
Add beans.
Cover and cook until beans are tender. Serves 4.

title: valentine's day cookie(danish butter cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks and flour.
Roll out and cut into thin hearts.
Bake at 350° until slightly browned.

title: sausage and potato loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together and pat into greased loaf pan. Place pan on a cookie sheet to catch possible drips and cover loosely with foil.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours, draining off grease occasionally.
Remove from pan and slice to serve.

title: shortcut chili con carne
directions: In skillet or slow-cooking pot with browning unit, break up beef with fork and cook until lightly browned.
Pour off excess fat.
In slow-cooking pot, combine meat with onion, salt, tomato sauce and kidney beans.
Cover and cook on high for 2 to 3 hours. Remove bay leaf.
Makes 6 to 7 servings.

title: oatmeal chewy
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients 1 minute.
Then add oatmeal, cocoa and vanilla.
Add nuts or raisins and drop on wax paper.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to 250°, then add margarine and peanuts
and cook to 310°.	(Will be light brown.) Remove from heat. Add vanilla and soda.
Stir fast; no lumps.
Foams up quick.
Pour quickly onto buttered cookie sheet; don't try to spread. Cool, then break.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix well and spread into a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: cheesy mashed potatoes
directions: In a Dutch oven, add water to unpeeled potatoes just to cover. Sprinkle with salt.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 35 minutes or until almost tender; drain.
Cool slightly; peel and shred potatoes with a grater.
In a large mixing bowl, combine potatoes, cheese and butter; stir until butter melts completely.
Stir in sour cream, green onion, 1/2 teaspoon of salt and the pepper.
Transfer to a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until heated through.
Before serving, sprinkle with paprika.

title: pineapple-mandarin cooler
directions: Drain mandarins and pineapple, set aside syrup.
In separate bowls, mix fruits together and fruit syrups together.
Fill sherbet glasses 2/3 full with the fruit mixture.
Add a scoop of sherbet to each glass.
Spoon 2 tablespoons of the mixed syrup over each portion.
Serves 4.

title: marzetti
directions: Cook onion and pepper with pork.
Simmer with cover on. Do not brown.
Mix pork mixture and remaining ingredients all together. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: warm chicken taco salad
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips and saute in 1/4 cup Miracle Whip salad dressing.
Stir in remaining 1/4 cup dressing, tomato and taco seasoning mix.
Cook 5 minutes or until chicken is cooked through. Layer on large platter tortilla chips, lettuce and chicken mixture. Top with cheese, olives and green onions.
Or can be served on heated tortilla shells.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Brown ground beef.
Drain well.
Add peas, tomatoes and rice.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Top with grated cheese.
Heat until melted.
Good with salad and corn bread.

title: neapolitan cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the cake mix, water, oil and eggs. Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Divide batter into 3 equal portions. Pour one portion into a greased 10-inch fluted tube pan. Stir red food coloring into another portion. Carefully spoon into pan. Stir chocolate syrup and cocoa into remaining batter. Carefully spoon into pan. DO NOT SWIRL. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from the pan to a wire rack to cool completely. Dust with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: cranberry pumpkin muffins
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients and set aside.
Beat oil with eggs and pumpkin until well blended.
Add pumpkin mix all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir until just moistened.
Fold in cranberries.
Spoon batter into 18 paper lined muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 2 eggs.
Stir until well blended. Beat one minute.
Spread batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Beat in remaining 2 eggs and vanilla.
Set aside 1/2 cup xx sugar.
Beat remaining xx sugar into cheese.
Pour over cake batter in pan. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake pulls away from side of pan.
Cool for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar which was set aside.

title: company rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese with butter. Add flour and salt. Make into small biscuits. Bake at 425° about 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Wash
ribs;
place in baking dish, meaty side up.
Salt and pepper.
Place
onion on top of ribs.
Mix Barbecue Sauce and pour over ribs.

title: chefs choice fruit salad
directions: Line a large salad bowl with romaine leaves.
Place torn greens in center of bowl.
Arrange apple slices around edge. Sprinkle with coconut.
Arrange raisins, almonds and carrot in a circular design atop lettuce.
Cover and chill.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add noodles, soups, sour cream and corn.
Mix well.
Pour into 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with cheese or bread crumbs.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: ham and asparagus scallop
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place 2 slices toast in the bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, cutting bread, if necessary.
Arrange asparagus, egg slices and ham over the bread.
Repeat layers. Combine cheese and Worcestershire sauce and pour over the casserole.
Mix crumbs and butter; sprinkle over the top.
Bake 12 minutes or until browned.
Serves 4.

title: three-in-one dip
directions: Mix all ingredients at medium speed until well blended. Refrigerate.
Serve hot or cold.
To heat, microwave on High. Good with tortilla chips or breaded fried vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: broccoli-shrimp stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub and pierce potatoes, wrap in microwave safe paper towel. Arrange 1 inch apart in microwave and cook on high 6 to 8 minutes, turning once. Let stand 2 minutes. With a fork, pierce the skin in the shape of a cross. Press the ends of the potato towards the center, lifting and fluffing the meat of the potato. Combine broccoli and onions in a 9 inch pie plate, cover with plastic wrap and microwave at high 3 to 4 minutes or until tender, drain. Combine chicken broth, soy sauce, vinegar and cornstarch in a 4 cup measure, microwave uncovered for 2 to 3 minutes, or until slightly thickened. Pour sauce over broccoli, stir in cooked shrimp and pimento. Spoon mixture over potatoes.

title: cornmeal scrapple
directions: In a saucepan, combine the cornmeal, milk, sugar and salt. Gradually stir in water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat; cook, covered, 10 minutes longer or until very thick, stirring occasionally.
Remove from the heat and stir in sausage.
Pour into a greased 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pan (the pan will be very full).
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.
To serve, unmold, and cut into 1/3-inch slices.
Dip both sides in flour.
In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat; brown scrapple on both sides.
Serve with maple syrup if desired. Yields 6 servings.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add blueberries, lemon juice and water.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir until thickened.
Makes 2 cups.
Serve over pancakes, French toast or waffles.

title: auntie's pound cake
directions: Place all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat at high speed for 5 minutes.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn out and wrap in foil until cool.
Ice as desired.

title: barbecued potatoes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add potatoes, tossing to coat. Spread potatoes evenly on a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until tender.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Saute ground beef until browned; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
Place each biscuit in greased muffin tin, pressing to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon mixture into cups and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
Makes 12 servings.

title: frank's durn good chicken soup starter(with zero added salt and near zero fat.)
directions: As the chicken is timing out on the boil, get out your trusty 8 to 10-quart soup pot.
Put about 3 quarts of water in it and put the heat on full (you are going to be adding so many ingredients that it won't boil right away).
Add ingredients to soup pot.

title: shrimp in wine sauce
directions: Add all ingredients except shrimp together.
Simmer until rice is hot.
Add shrimp.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes each side.
Serve over yellow rice.

title: jerry's favorite chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake mix in three 8-inch round cake pans.
Add powdered frosting to Cool Whip, adding as much chocolate as desired.
Frost cake layers, including top and sides with mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, sifted flour, baking powder and pineapple juice.
Beat the mixture for 20 minutes vigorously and then add candied cherries, chopped fine; also, candied pineapple and nuts.
Bake slowly until done.

title: heavenly bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and garlic.
Drain and set aside. Mix remaining ingredients and add these to beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 9-inch glass baking dish. Makes 4 servings.

title: meat pie
directions: Make pie crusts.
Brown hamburger and pork together.
In large bowl, combine meat and stuffing; mix.
Make onion soup according to package directions; add cheese to melt.
When at a boil, add to meat mixture; mix.
Place in ready pie crusts and cover with another crust.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until well browned.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: Note:
You may substitute with blueberry pie filling.

title: aunt marie's refrigerator pickles
directions: Boil vinegar and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Cool completely.
