Mix cucumbers, salt and onions.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 1/2 hours, then drain.
Add vinegar mixture. Place mixture in a glass or plastic container and refrigerate. Keeps for a long time.

title: macaroni cheese deluxe
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain well.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, egg, salt and pepper.
Add cheese and mix well.
Stir in cooked macaroni.
Turn into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
I make this a day before and chill in fridge until ready to bake (overnight).

title: vegan ala casserole
directions: Mix all contents together.
Roll into walnut sized balls. Freeze before baking.
Cover with sauce.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 20.

title: sausage, peppers and onions
directions: Cut sausage in 4-inch lengths and brown completely.
Set aside.
Empty cans of tomatoes into large kettle or crock-pot. Add all spices and bring to a boil.
Turn heat back to simmer. Add sausage and pan drippings.
Cut green peppers and onions into large slices and add to sauce.
Cover and cook 6 hours.
Taste and add additional spice if needed throughout cooking time.

title: squash pickles
directions: Place squash, onions and pepper in layers.
Salt as if for cooking.
Let stand 1 hour, then drain.
Heat other ingredients and pour over squash.
Bring to a boil. Seal in hot jars.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Mix beans, barbecue sauce, chili powder, hot sauce, brown sugar, cinnamon or allspice and mustard in large bowl or casserole dish.
Steam bell pepper, onion and celery or microwave for 3 minutes.
Add to bean mixture.
Stir in prepared ground beef. Break up 1/2 of bacon in bite sized pieces.
Stir into bean mixture.
Place remaining bacon strips on top of bean mixture. Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and vanilla together.
Add milk and flour mixture alternately with sugar mixture.
Chill thoroughly.
Roll out on floured board and cut.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: snappy salmon pie
directions: Combine rice, egg and cheese; mix well.
Firmly press into bottom and sides of a greased 9-inch pan.
Combine rest of ingredients and mix well.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in an airtight container. Refrigerate.

title: pink peppermint dip
directions: Gently stir mints into whipped topping in small bowl. Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Serve as a dip for cookies and fruit.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.
Good dip for Christmas.

title: chuck roast paprika
directions: Wash roast; pat dry.
Sprinkle with the paprika; brown on each side in 3 tablespoons cooking oil.
Cover with water; simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add pepper, onion and tomato; cook 30 more minutes. Remove roast from pot.
Thicken gravy with water and flour mixture to desired thickness.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Roll dough out to 8 x 10-inch size. Brush combined seasonings on dough. (Save some to brush on top later.) Arrange pepperoni on top; cover with cheese and roll up like a jelly roll. Brush remaining seasonings on top of pepperoni roll. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes on a cookie sheet. Cool 20 minutes before cutting.

title: no-cholesterol apple cake
directions: Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick coating; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl combine sugars, oil and egg whites. Beat with a wooden spoon until well blended.
Add flours, oat bran, baking soda, cinnamon and allspice or nutmeg; stir just until moistened.
Stir in shredded apples.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
If desired, sift powdered sugar atop cake.
Makes 16 servings.

title: chicken las vegas
directions: Mix soups with 1/2 can of water.
Season flour with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Dip chicken in milk; roll in flour and brown lightly in small amount of oil.
Place chicken in greased casserole; put cheese on top and pour soup mixture over all.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients in a large bowl; form into loaf pan.
Place in a pan larger than the meat loaf. Coat top and sides with ketchup.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Carefully pour off fat.

title: corn chowder with fresh herbs and smoked ham
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine broth, onion and carrot.
Tie together bay leaf and fresh herbs to make bouquet garni.
Add to saucepan and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Remove herbs.
Dice enough of the potatoes to make 1 cup.
Set aside.
Add the remaining potatoes and 1 can of the corn to the saucepan.
Puree with electric blender in batches until smooth. Return to saucepan.
Stir in diced potatoes, the remaining corn and half and half into saucepan.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in pimentos and parsley.
Season with pepper, if desired.
Ladle into bowls.
Garnish with ham and chopped parsley.

title: green chilies casserole
directions: Put bread in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Add Cheddar cheese and crumbled bacon.
Sprinkle with green chilies on top.
Add grated Jack cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and spices together and pour over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 8 or 10.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini until tender.
Meanwhile saute carrots and onions in a little butter until limp.
Add soup and sour cream. Add 3/4 cup croutons and zucchini, stirring gently.
Pour into 2-quart greased casserole.
Sprinkle remaining croutons on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine zucchini, onions and salt and let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain. Add rest of ingredients and put all in large kettle. Bring to a boil; simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally, 30 minutes or until of desired consistency.
Place in clean sterilized jars and process in water bath for 5 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine sugar, paprika, salt and dry mustard.
Slowly stir in vinegar and olive oil.
Beat the dressing until thoroughly mixed, approximately 3 to 5 minutes.

title: asparagus quiche
directions: Chop mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Shred cheese; mix and put into a 10-inch pie plate.
Mix Bisquick, milk, eggs and pepper in blender; pour over all vegetables.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Butter a 1 1/2 qt. casserole.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Beat baking mix, eggs, milk and salt until smooth.
Mix in broccoli and cheese.
Bake 1 hr. or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cheesy chicken pitas
directions: Toss peppers and onion together in a small bowl.
Spray a small frying pan with cooking spray.
Cook garlic and chicken until thoroughly heated.
For each pita half, fill with a layer of chicken strips, 2 halves of cheese and 1/4 cup pepper and onion mixture.
Cover loosely.
Microwave on High for 30 seconds or until cheese is melted.
Add lettuce and serve with sour cream. Makes 4 pitas.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together, then add shortening, egg, molasses,
water and vinegar.
Mix well.
Then roll out. Bake at 375° on cookie sheet about 10 to 15 minutes.
Leave on tray about 1/2 minute.
Then remove to cooling rack.

title: rice
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over rice.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook; keep stirring until it comes to a boil.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour over 6 quarts of hot popcorn. Mix well.
Pour on 2 pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: little reubens
directions: Mix all together and add enough Thousand Island or Miracle Whip salad dressing (approximately 1/3 cup) until it holds together. Put a teaspoonful on a rye cracker or a Triscuit.
Put in microwave or under broiler until the cheese melts.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix and bake immediately for maximum lightness.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburger, onion and seasoning together.
Layer hamburger, beans, soup, milk and potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.
Then add grated cheese. Bake for 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: black cherry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and mix with blender or mixer.
When mixture thickens slightly, stir in sour cream.
Swirl it in and refrigerate.
Top with sour cream.

title: sourdough bread(made from basic sourdough starter)
directions: Combine ingredients in order of water, sugar, salt, oil and flour, using only enough flour to make dough so that it can be handled.
Knead until smooth on lightly floured board. Place in greased bowl and allow to rise.
This takes longer then regular yeast dough.
Knead down and allow to rise again.
Divide into 4 parts. Shape and place into greased loaf pans and allow to rise again. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding noodles last so they will remain crisp.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients together, then cook (boil for 1 minute). Remove from stove.
Add the peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop onto wax paper until cool.
Serve at once.

title: cuban coffee
directions: Combine cream and coffee in a saucepan and simmer for 5 minutes.
Strain through a fine sieve and pour into cups.
Top with whipped cream and serve with sugar.
Serves 4.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Mix the last 10 ingredients and pour over 5 cups carrots, sliced, cooked and cooled, 1 medium onion, sliced into rings and 1 medium green pepper thinly sliced.
Mix and refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Keeps a long time in the refrigerator.

title: french herbed chicken
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in hot fat.
Season with salt and pepper and place in 2-quart casserole.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients except celery and bay leaf.
Pour over chicken; tuck in celery and bay leaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Remove bay leaf and celery.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours.
Just before serving, drain salad.
Yields 6 servings. Has 40 calories per serving.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Mix first (4) four ingredients together; let stand 1 hour.

title: fourth of july fruit salad
directions: Slice the watermelon lengthwise so that one piece is slightly larger than the other.
The larger piece will be the fruit bowl for the salad.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix vanilla wafers with 1 stick melted oleo; press in pan for crust.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, 1/2 stick oleo and milk. Beat until smooth.
Spread mixture over crust.

title: magic lemon pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, milk, lemon juice and lemon extract and pour into pie crust.
Whip egg whites, adding 1 tablespoon sugar one at a time for meringue.

title: hot and sour meatballs
directions: Combine picante sauce and cranberries and heat in saucepan on stove.
Pour over meatballs and serve.

title: blueberry-pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Combine pumpkin and evaporated milk.
Cream shortening and sugar; add egg.
Add flour mixture alternately with pumpkin mixture, beating well after each addition.
Combine blueberries and flour.
Gently stir into batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Use 13 x 9-inch pan.
Butter generously.
Bake mixture until golden brown at 350° for 30 minutes on upper rack in oven.
Cool. Cut into bite-size squares.
Package and freeze.
When ready to serve, be sure they are completely thawed.
Bake again at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot on picks.

title: hot buttered rum mix
directions: Mix brown sugar in with softened butter.
Add powdered sugar and mix well.
Add spices and mix well.
Add ice cream.
Heat mixture until creamy.
Chill for 2 hours.
Can be frozen.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan.
Cook and stir until sugar dissolves.
Bring to a boil and cook 3 minutes.
Gradually add hot syrup to the eggs, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell; arrange pecan halves on filling. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until pie is set.
Cool.

title: cashew and noodle casserole
directions: Cut drained tender bits in fourths, bread with meal and brown in hot oil.
Saute mushrooms, celery and onion in corn oil.
Add browned entree pieces and mix well.
Place in oiled casserole and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: yellow and green squash
directions: Cut up yellow and green squash in rounds.
Make sauce by sauteing in butter the onion.
Add squash to sauce.
Season and cook under low flame for 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Spread on cake when taken from oven.

title: green onion gelatin salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Allow jello to start to set.
Stir once again and allow to set.

title: cheese cake
directions: Butter and flour a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Heat oven to 350°. Mix together the Ricotta cheese and cream cheese.
Add flour, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla, beating well.
Blend in eggs, one at a time, using slow speed of mixer.
Gently add sour cream, then pour mixture into prepared pan.
Dust with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven; leave cake in for 4 to 5 hours. Remove from oven and refrigerate.

title: creamy cole slaw dressing
directions: Blend well with wire whisk.

title: mom's veggie casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in casserole dish.
Melt margarine.
Add crushed Ritz crackers; top casserole with this. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes, until brown and bubbly.

title: dukhobor(borscht)
directions: Place 1/4 pound of butter and onion in a large saucepan and simmer until onion is shiny.
Add tomatoes, finely grated carrot, 1/2 grated beet and 1/2 chopped green pepper and boil 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
Place 3 quarts boiling water in a large kettle. Add 3 potatoes, cut in half, remaining beet, diced carrot, diced celery and salt.
Boil until potatoes are done. Remove potatoes and mash.
Add the rest of the butter and the cream. Add 3 diced potatoes and let boil for 1 minute, then add boiled tomato mixture, shredded cabbage and mashed potatoes.
Bring to a boil. Add chopped green pepper, dill and black pepper.
Remove from heat. Cover with lid. Serve hot.

title: waffle cookies
directions: Melt
margarine
and chocolate together.
Beat together eggs, sugar, vanilla, flour and salt.
Mix in melted margarine and chocolate.
Drop
teaspoon
onto
hot waffle iron and bake 1 minute.
Frost with Waffle Cookie Frosting.

title: corn muffin
directions: Mix egg, oil (or creamed shortening) and milk.
Add flour sifted with salt and baking powder.
Add meal.
Grease muffin tins.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions.
Mix hamburger, macaroni and cheese and soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar, molasses and eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients to creamed mixture.
Form dough into balls. Roll dough balls in white sugar.
Bake at 325° for 17 minutes. Yields 50 cookies.

title: veggie crescent hors d'oeuvres
directions: Can buy broccoli and cauliflower already cut in salad section.

title: orange fluff
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water.
Stir in orange juice and cool. Add oranges and pineapple.
Pour into a 13 x 13-inch dish and congeal.
Beat pudding with milk until slightly firm.
Fold whipping cream into pudding mix.
Spread over congealed orange salad.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: raw apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in unbaked deep dish pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: golden crusted steak
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl combine all ingredients but steak.
Arrange steak on rack in broiler pan.
Press onion mixture on top and sides of steak.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes or until steak is done.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: In large bowl, mix pineapple with marshmallows.
Cover and set aside.
In saucepan, mix juice, sugar, flour, egg and vinegar; cook until thickened, stirring with a wire whisk.
Cool completely.
Combine with Cool Whip.
Fold into pineapple-marshmallows.
Add nuts and apples.

title: easy diet cobbler
directions: Pour melted butter in a 9-inch square pan.
Mix flour and milk; pour over butter.
Add sweetener to apples or fruit and put over mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: reuben sandwich spread
directions: Combine and mix well in casserole dish. May also put in small slow cooker. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot all through. Spread on rye bread; may toast bread.
Great to serve on a hors d'oeuvre table.

title: vacuum cleaner cookies
directions: Combine margarine, cake mix and 1 egg.
Pat into greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Beat remaining 2 eggs, cream cheese and sugar.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour over the cake mix in pan. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Enjoy!

title: tamale and corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Combine onion, pepper, corn, tamales and seasonings.
Taste and adjust seasonings to taste.
Sprinkle with thick layer of grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O with boiling water.
Allow to partially congeal and add oranges, cranberry sauce and pineapple with juice.
Stir into partially congealed gelatin and chill.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Yields 6 rolls.

title: quick raspberry salad
directions: Empty gelatin into bowl. Add boiling water and stir well until dissolved. Add ice cream and stir until melted. Add undrained pineapple, orange juice and walnuts.
Turn into a mold.
Chill. As mixture cools, it separates.
Serve as a salad or dessert.

title: crazy corn
directions: Boil fresh corn cobs. Spread with mayonnaise while hot and sprinkle with parmesan cheese.

title: hot apple drink
directions: Melt red hots in juice until hot.
Serve.
Good for a cold winter night.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: butterfields' mushroom soup
directions: Saute leeks and mushrooms in butter without browning until soft.
Remove from heat and mix in flour.
Add broth and wine; bring to a boil.
Add cream and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add seasonings and sherry to taste.
Serves six.

title: try me cake
directions: Put all ingredients in 1 bowl and mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
It is a moist cake.

title: home brew (beer)
directions: Note:
Need 10 gallon crock, bottle caper, bottle caps (crown), 24 quart bottles, 4 foot tubing and one 2 x 4 x 4-inch.

title: intoxicated chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
In a large skillet, heat the butter and oil; brown the chicken on both sides.
Add Jack Daniels and carefully ignite, shaking the skillet until flames go out.
Add the shallots and cook for 1 minute.
Add thyme, parsley and water; cover skillet and cook over low heat, turning occasionally, 25 to 35 minutes.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix together in large bowl the cake mix, oil, apricot nectar, Jell-O and eggs.
Pour into greased tube pan and cook until done at 300°.
Mix lemon juice and powdered sugar and pour over cake as soon as you remove it from oven.
Let cool in pan.
If desired, add butter in sauce.

title: fried apple rings
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together the butter and sugar. Add the eggs; beat until light and fluffy.
Add the almond extract.
Stir in the flour and baking powder; mix until smooth. Butter a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Turn the mixture into the pan. Spoon the pie filling into the cake, in 16 spots, spacing 4 spoonfuls evenly in each direction.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until golden and cake tests done.
Filling will sink into the cake while baking.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Pour into greased pan (9 x 12-inch).

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onions in Wesson oil.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook on medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture cooks down about 1/2-inch in pan.

title: baptist punch
directions: Mix half grape juice and half Sprite in quantity needed for your party.
Pour over ice and serve.

title: taco dip
directions: Thoroughly mix the cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning. Spread over a large round platter, plate or tray.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, top with the rest of the ingredients in the order given.
Garnish with olives.
Sprinkle a little taco sauce over all.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and chill.
Best when made the day before.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine sugar and cornstarch in a large bowl.
Mix, pressing out any lumps.
Stir in lemon peel.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in lemon juice.
Blend in butter.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake until puffed and golden brown, 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool to room temperature before using.
Filling will thicken, fall somewhat and acquire jelly like texture as it cools.

title: st.  petersburg pork chops(russia)
directions: Tenderize pork chops lightly with a mallet and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Melt all the butter but 2 Tbsp. in a large skillet and cook the pork chops until done. Remove to a serving dish. Place mushrooms in a small skillet with remaining butter and fry for 2-3 minutes. Add tomatoes and garlic, cook 2-3 more minutes. Place mushroom and tomato mix and any remaining butter on each chop. Serve hot. Serves 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Soften butter. Add sugar, syrup and salt.
Beat until blended. Beat eggs and add.
Fold in pecans and add vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: dee's chicken casserole
directions: In the bottom of a large casserole, place 1 package of crushed Ritz crackers, a mixture of chicken pieces, soup and sour cream, then another package of crushed Ritz crackers mixed with 1 stick melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 30 minutes until hot.
Make 4 to 6 servings.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain artichokes; cut into squares. Cook spinach according to directions; drain.
Combine cream cheese and butter in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat until melted, stirring constantly.
Layer artichokes, spinach, cream cheese mixture and bacon in an 8 x 8 square casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: busy day stew
directions: Place all ingredients together in a Dutch oven.
Cover tightly.
Do not stir.
Place in a 250° oven for 7 to 8 hours or place in crock-pot on low heat for 7 to 8 hours.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Peel, core and cut pineapple crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Set 5 slices aside, reserving remaining pineapple for another use.
Combine 1 tablespoon margarine and brown sugar in a small saucepan.
Stir well.
Place over medium heat and cook 1 minute.
Add pineapple juice.
Cook an additional minute, stirring constantly.
Spread evenly into an 8-inch round cake pan.
Sprinkle walnuts around outside edge of pan.
Arrange pineapple slices in a single layer over brown sugar mixture.
Set aside.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix dressing, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Chill.
Bake corn bread.
Cool and crumble.
Chop bell pepper, green onion and tomato.

title: lauren's grandma's meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; continue beating and add cream of tartar, salt and sugar, a little at a time.
Continue beating until it holds peaks.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons onto a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes (try to lift off from the cookie sheet; if you can lift off and the cookie does not stick to the pan then it is done).

title: chicken au vin
directions: Bone chicken and place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with a little salt.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: vegetarian one pot
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium-size saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer until the rice is cooked and most of the liquid is absorbed, 5 to 20 minutes, depending on the kind of rice used. Vegetables and seasonings can be added to taste.
Onion or bell peppers are especially good.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into pan.
Bake until golden brown on top (about 25 minutes).
Cut into 1 x 1-inch squares.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 4 dozen appetizers.

title: orange yogurt popsicles
directions: First, make a regular batch of yogurt, then mix together orange juice, vanilla and honey, then beat with yogurt.
Put into 5 ounce paper cups.
Freeze a little, then stick sticks into the middle. Freeze completely.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Arrange potato wedges peel side down in shallow baking pan. Mix remaining ingredients and brush over potatoes.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Baste occasionally with oil mixture.

title: summer sausage
directions: Sprinkle dry ingredients over meat.
Put liquid smoke into the water, then mix all ingredients.
Shape into 3-inch rolls.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate 24 hours.
Lay in pan and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: apple or peach crisp
directions: Slice fruit in a 10-inch buttered pan or casserole dish, and cover with 1/4 cup sugar.
Cream the butter and sugar, and then add beaten egg.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture and spread over fruit.
Bake in a moderate oven, 350°, for 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with cream.

title: baked stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brush dirt off mushrooms.
Remove stems.
Chop stems fine. Saute stems and garlic in butter.
Add spices and sherry.
Remove from heat.
Stir in bread crumbs and cheese (add crabmeat).
Stuff into caps.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Blend all together, folding in miniature marshmallows, in a large bowl.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In salted water, cook spaghetti until tender; drain and rinse with hot water.
Drain mushrooms and save liquid.
Melt butter and saute onion.
Add seasonings and mushroom liquid.
Blend in soup. Stir until smooth.
Gradually add evaporated milk, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
In casserole pan, mix spaghetti, mushrooms, pimento and chicken.
Pour in sauce and mix. Top with cheese.
Bake in oven at 350°
until it bubbles, about 30 minutes.

title: pat's quiche-chile cheese appetizer
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 pan.
Beat eggs; add flour, baking powder and salt.
Pour remaining butter in mixing bowl; add the rest of ingredients.
Put in pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° for 35 minutes.
No cover.

title: chocolate chip coconut pecan cookies
directions: Beat margarine, sugar, vanilla and eggs until light and fluffy. Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in nuts, chips and coconut.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart onto cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash until just tender with water halfway up (about 10 minutes).
Beat eggs, mayonnaise, oleo, cheese and green pepper. Fold in zucchini and onion.
Salt and pepper.
Add bread crumbs. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add corn bread mix last.
Pour into a large 2 to 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: white castle's
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Spread mixture on prepared cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Cut in small squares and serve on miniature party buns. Serve with sauted onions and pickles if desired.

title: china-town moon cake(in honor broodmare, "doc's ivy")
directions: Prepare cake mix by package directions, adding tea and rind of lemon to the batter.
Bake in greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans; remove from pans and cool on rack.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Punch holes in brownies and pour Kahlua over them.
Crumble 1/2 brownies in bottom of glass serving bowl.
Layer all items. Chill to set.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except cucumber, mixing until well blended.
Stir in cucumber.
Chill several hours or overnight. Serve with chips or veggies.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: salmon or tuna cream cheese spread
directions: In large bowl, beat together cream cheese, horseradish, smoked barbecue sauce, lemon juice, pickle relish, chopped walnuts and chopped green onions.
Add drained and boned salmon or tuna.
Beat well.
Put in covered dish and refrigerate until used.
Spread on crackers, bread or vegetable slices.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over boiling water. Combine broken pretzels and peanuts; add to melted chocolate. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Candy will harden and be ready to eat in 10 minutes.

title: ziti with chicken and broccoli
directions: Place the chicken breasts, one at a time, on a flat surface. Using a sharp knife, cut the breasts in half, then lengthwise into thin strips, about 1/2-inch thick.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit with pie filling.
Keep refrigerated.
Will keep for approximately 1 week.

title: grandma's chocolate waffles
directions: Melt butter over medium heat.
Add chocolate square and melt. Pour in cup of sugar and mix in eggs.
Pour this mixture into mixing bowl.
Add milk and the flour; monitor the amount of flour so that mixture resembles the consistency of pancake batter. Pour batter in hot waffle iron; cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Eat with syrup or applesauce.

title: lasagna
directions: Fry hamburger.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, enough to cover the meat thoroughly.
Set rest aside.
Cook noodles.
Drain.
In square 9 x 13-inch pan, put one layer of noodles.
Add some hamburger on top and spread around.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top of that.
Continue with noodles, meat and cheese until you get to the top of the pan.
(Should have 3 to 4 layers.)
Take sauce and pour around the outside of the pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour or until cheese is melted on top.

title: honeycomb pudding
directions: Mix together the sugar, molasses and flour.
Heat together the butter and milk.
When hot, add soda and blend with sugar, flour and molasses.
Add the well-beaten eggs last.
Steam 1 1/2 hours. Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: sweet dill slices
directions: Drain dill pickles.
Combine sugar and vinegar and boil.
Cool and pour over pickles.

title: chocolate whip
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over 1/4 cup cold water.
Combine chocolate, milk, sugar and salt in top of double boiler.
Heat over hot water, stirring occasionally, until chocolate is melted.
Stir in softened gelatin.
Heat until melted.
Add vanilla.

title: dole raisin pineapple muffins
directions: Beat sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, juice and orange peel.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir into juice mixture until moistened.
Spoon batter in 6 muffin cups, coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool on rack and serve warm.
Makes 6 large muffins.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together cream cheese, 2/3 cup sugar and almond extract until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one at low speed until blended.
Pour into ungreased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Stir together sour cream, 3 tablespoons sugar and vanilla.
Carefully spread atop hot pie. Cool.
Cover and chill.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, egg and molasses thoroughly in a bowl.
Stir flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt together in another bowl.
Mix these dry ingredients into the shortening mixture.
Chill dough in refrigerator 2 hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a baking sheet. Roll teaspoonfuls of chilled dough into balls the size of large walnuts.
Dip tops into sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: gram's broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; save 1/3 cup of water. In a large pot, combine butter, onion and flour; cook until thick. Blend in milk, gradually.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Add broccoli and 1/3 cup saved water.
Cook until heated.
Add cheese and melt, to taste.

title: dump cake
directions: Spoon cherry pie filling on bottom of Pam sprayed Pyrex dish. Spread pineapple over pie filling. Sprinkle "dry" cake mix over pineapple.
Pour melted oleo evenly over all.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Everyone likes this.

title: favorite frosting
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in a saucepan on medium heat until they cook to a thick solid mass (like paste).
Cool until cold. Add the margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Beat well until very creamy and fluffy.

title: parmesan rolls(cloverleaf)
directions: Prepare hot roll mix according to package directions. Divide dough into 12 portions. Divide each portion into 3 pieces. Shape each piece into a ball. Place 3 balls each into well-greased muffin tins. Brush with butter. Combine Parmesan with garlic powder and sprinkle over top of dough. Cover and let rise in a warm place for 12 to 15 minutes. Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt butter
in saucepan and slowly stir sugar into it. Mix vinegar with corn meal and add to mixture.
Slightly cool, add slightly
beaten
eggs.
Stir
well
and pour into pie pan lined with
uncooked
pastry.
Bake
at
for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 275° and cook for 40 minutes.

title: cherry tortes
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together, then add cherries, egg and butter.
Put in 13 x 9-inch floured pan.
Bake 3/4 hour at 350°.

title: lucille's homemade grape juice
directions: Place sugar and grapes in a quart jar and fill with boiling water.
Process in water bath canner 20 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into buttered casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour dawg bites
directions: Broil wieners and cut into pieces.
Cool slightly.
In boiler over medium heat, cook jelly until turns to liquid.
Add mustard to taste.
Add sliced wieners.
Heat to boiling, then cook about 5 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and transfer to crock-pot or chafing dish to keep warm while serving.

title: garbage
directions: Drain all fruit juices and mix all ingredients together. Chill.

title: spaghetti bolognese
directions: In a large skillet, brown turkey or chicken; drain.
Add onions, carrots and garlic.
Cook, stirring for 5 minutes until onion is tender.
Add all ingredients except spaghetti.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, in boiling salt water, cook spaghetti until tender.
Drain, put into a serving bowl, and pour the sauce over.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: one pan fast fixing applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and pour oil in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place yellow cake, eggs and applesauce in pan.
Scrape sides and bottom of pan, blend with fork or spoon.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
If desired, sprinkle with 4X sugar.
Cut and serve directly from pan.

title: pumpkin butter(canning)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook 15 minutes.
Pour into sterilized 4-ounce canning jars.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes 15 jars.

title: string beans german fashion
directions: Wash; remove the strings, then cut each pod through twice lengthwise.
Then into 2-inch lengths.
Parboil the beans 30 minutes.
Saute in a stew pan with the butter and seasonings. Cook until butter is absorbed, then add stock and lemon juice. Simmer until perfectly tender.

title: cathy's enchilada casserole
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients, cream of mushroom soup and 1 1/4 cups water in saucepan.
Warm over low heat.
Brown ground beef, onion and garlic in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Add olives, salt and 1/2 cup tomato mixture.
Mix well.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening. Add brown sugar.
Stir until well mixed.
Allow to cool slightly. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add dry ingredients, then nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake in greased pan (10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch) at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bountiful rice
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and spices.
Layer with other ingredients in a large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls out in a pizza pan.
Pour the raw eggs on the crescent rolls.
Sprinkle the cooked sausage on top of the raw eggs.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients but mushrooms in saucepan; bring to boil.
Remove from heat and add 2 pounds sliced mushrooms. Marinate several days.
Mix well occasionally.

title: balsamic roasted new potatoes
directions: Heat olive oil in a pan.
Add quartered potatoes, garlic and shallots.
Saute and toss.
Add spices and toss.
Place all on a baking sheet.
Spread in a single layer.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ground beef, mushroom soup and onion soup mix together.
Place in a greased casserole dish. Cover and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
When ground beef is done, put Tater Tots on top and bake until Tater Tots are done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and sour cream; set aside.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Pour Cool Whip mixture over it.
Stir.
Chill well.

title: casserole of chicken and broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Dice chicken; shred cheese.
Place broccoli in baking dish.
Cover with diced chicken and shredded cheese.
Put remaining ingredients into a blender; mix.
Pour mixture over cheese.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch oblong baking dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamy straw-bana shakes
directions: Peel and cut up bananas.
Wrap in foil then freeze about 1 hour or until firm.
In a blender container combine bananas, milk, berries and cottage cheese.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Add ice cubes, then cover and blend until smooth.
Garnish each glass with a fresh strawberry if desired.
Makes 4 (8-ounce) servings.

title: chicken a la budapest
directions: Wash and pat dry each breast.
Melt butter in long baking dish. Place chicken pieces on the bottom, flesh side down.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Arrange side by side; divide onions and garlic evenly and place between or under chicken pieces.
Combine sour cream with Worcestershire sauce and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours. After 30 minutes, add half of the wine; bake 20 minutes more.
Add remaining wine.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form into a ball.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes if desired.

title: mock mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Form into 2-inch patties and fry slowly until lightly browned.
This is an excellent substitute for fresh mushrooms!

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Beat the egg. Add brown sugar and vanilla.
Mix the chocolate and shortening.
Melt over hot water. Add flour, soda and salt. Mix. Add milk.
Nuts may be added. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Spray cookie sheet with vegetable spray.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange crackers on large cookie sheet with edges touching. Fill all spaces with crackers.
Boil butter, sugar and nuts 2 minutes at rapid boil. Remove from heat.
Spoon evenly over crackers. Bake 10 minutes (about). Check frequently since ovens vary and these burn quickly. Cut by pressing spatula into warm cookies. Allow to cool.

title: fruit tart
directions: Soften cookie dough and press evenly onto pizza pan. Bake according to directions. Make pudding according to directions and spread on cooled cookie. Arrange fruit in concentric circles. Brush with melted apple jelly to glaze. Chill.

title: stove-top apple butter
directions: In a 6 to 8-quart heavy kettle, bring apples and water to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until apples are tender. Press cooked apples through a colander or food mill. Discard peels. Return pureed apples to the kettle. Stir in remaining ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, stirring frequently, until the consistency is very thick and the color is dark brown, about 8 hours. Freeze in containers or preserve using your favorite method. Yield: 4 to 6 cups.

title: chicken adobo(a filipino main dish)
directions: Combine chicken, vinegar, 1 tablespoon of the garlic, bay leaves, soy sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Boil, then simmer, uncovered, for about 10 minutes or until tender.
If the sauce is reduced, add about 1/2 cup water.
Simmer, covered, until done (about 30 minutes more).
Remove meat from sauce.
Saute remaining garlic, in a skillet, in the oil, for a more pronounced flavor.
Add the chicken and fry until light brown.
Add the adobo sauce.
Serve with white rice.

title: shrimp and sausage jambalaya
directions: *A mixture of salt, red pepper, black pepper, chili powder and garlic powder.

title: quick tomato sauce
directions: Heat the oil
in a large saucepan over moderate heat.
Cook the garlic and onion with salt and pepper until soft, about 10 minutes. Add the tomatoes, tomato paste and bay leaves. Bring to a boil. Reduce to a simmer and cook, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Stir in basil and parsley. Cook an additional 5 minutes and remove from heat. Remove and discard bay leaves.
(May be kept, covered, in refrigerator up to 3 days).
Makes 5 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine cooked rice with chicken.
Mix in soup, peas, butter and onion in a 1-quart baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs or grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: the original chex mix
directions: Put Crispix, pretzels and peanuts in a large microwave-safe bowl.
Melt the oil, margarine, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt, onion salt and celery salt in microwave.
Mix well. Pour over cereal mixture and stir.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes. Stir well.
Microwave 2 minutes. Stir well.
Microwave 2 minutes. Stir well. Pour into paper bag to soak up grease. When cooled, put in airtight container.

title: chicken with soup
directions: Butter pan; lay chicken pieces in pan.
Salt to taste. Combine chicken soup and golden mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken. Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: broiled tomatoes(low-fat)
directions: Cut top off tomatoes; cut inside of tomatoes several times. Add seasonings and bread crumbs; top with Parmesan.
Place into sprayed baking dish.
Bake at 375° until tender to stick with fork or broil 10 to 15 minutes.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar and water until it reaches hard ball stage, 260°, on candy thermometer. Pour over egg white, beating constantly. Beat until stiff.
Fold in nuts and drop by spoonful on wax paper and cool.

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add eggs.
Blend in pumpkin, molasses, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and salt.
Stir in milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes until filling is set.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine in mixing bowl cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda, egg and softened yeast.
Add flour to form a stiff dough, beating well after each addition.
If you have trouble stirring in flour, you can knead it in.
Cover and let rise in warm place (85° to 90°) until light and double in size (50 to 60 minutes).
Stir down dough.
Turn into well-greased 8-inch round 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot olive dip
directions: Chop all ingredients and combine.
Oil and vinegar may be added, if desired.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: santa fe chicken stew
directions: In Dutch oven or large pot, heat oil.
Add onion and saut 2 to 3 minutes.
Add taco seasonings/spices, tomatoes, beans, corn and chilies; blend well.
In small bowl, gradually blend broth into cornstarch using a wire whisk.
Stir into stew.
Stir in cooked chicken.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. (Simmer longer for thicker stew.)
Garnish each serving with sour cream and Cheddar cheese if desired.

title: wassail
directions: Mix all together and simmer, except red hots.
Add red hots after simmering a few minutes or add a few with each serving.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir constantly over medium heat until thick.
Add 3 tablespoons butter and serve over hot biscuits.

title: burger and rice casserole(easy)
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole dish with the ingredients.
Bake with cover on for 1 hour.

title: spicy sugar cookies
directions: In a very large mixing bowl, cream sugar, shortening, vanilla and eggs.
Add sour cream, then all dry ingredients.
Blend well.

title: marshmallow marble top fudge
directions: Line 8 or 9-inch square pan with foil; set aside.
In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate chips and 2 tablespoons of butter with sweetened condensed milk, vanilla and salt.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly into prepared pan.
In medium saucepan over low heat, melt marshmallows with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Swirl through fudge with table knife. Refrigerate 2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Chop walnuts into medium size pieces. Set aside. Beat eggs. Gradually beat in sugar, then oil. Combine dry ingredients and add to first mixture alternately with zucchini. Stir in raisins, walnuts and vanilla. Turn into 2 greased and lightly floured loaf (9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch) pans. Bake on lowest rack at 350° for about 55 minutes or until done. Let stand about 10 minutes. Turn out and cool loaves. May be lightly glazed with powdered sugar mixed to spreading consistency with a little cream. Freezes well.

title: fruit salad
directions: Save 2 cups juice from fruits.
If you don't have 2 cups, use orange juice.
Prepare pudding.
When done, pour over fruit and chill.

title: fat-free chocolate therapy cake
directions: In a medium bowl, add ingredients one at a time, stirring well after each addition.
After adding marshmallow cream, mix until the marshmallow lumps are gone.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan that has been coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: chicken divan
directions: Steam chicken in a pan with water, onion, salt and pepper. Cook broccoli part way (not quite fork-tender).
Lay broccoli in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chicken on top of broccoli. Combine soup, milk, mayonnaise and cheese.
Pour over casserole. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: strawberry shortcakes
directions: Combine.
Pour batter in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: banana bread, cake or muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add each egg separately, mixing well.
Stir banana and lemon juice; add to mix.
Mix together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to cream mixture. Add nuts.

title: orange chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces into mixture of eggs and orange juice, then into mixture of bread crumbs, paprika, peel and 1 teaspoon salt.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together.
Beat the eggs in a large bowl and add the milk.
Stir in the dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
The batter should be about like pancake batter, you may need to add more milk.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Mix onion and butter in a skillet and simmer until onion is tender.
Add this mixture to mushrooms, mushroom soup, broccoli and garlic cheese.
Mix together over warm heat.
Serve warm over tortilla chips or use as a dip.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Mix the first eight ingredients and put all in 5 1/2-quart crock-pot.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Place over beans.
Do not stir.
Cook on high 4 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Separate and cut biscuits into quarters. Roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture and drop into Bundt pan. Sprinkle nuts over biscuits.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Stir together all ingredients. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with French bread slices, crackers or chips.

title: italian cookies
directions: Mix sugar and eggs in bowl.
In another bowl, blend together flour and butter, then add sugar mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Knead on floured board until dough is smooth and easy to handle.
Wrap in towel for 15 minutes.
Shape small amounts in crescents or small logs onto greased cookie sheet and bake approximately 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Dust with confectioners sugar or ice, if desired.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch pan (remove skin if wish). Place 1 slice Swiss cheese on top of each chicken breast.
Cover with mixture of soup and wine (water).
Spoon over chicken.
Cover with seasoned stuffing.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients.
Add lard, then milk and mix like pie crust.
Roll out like pie crust and spread with melted butter. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll like a jelly roll; cut and place in small muffin pans.
Dot each with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pecan fruit salad
directions: Toss all ingredients with 1/2 pint sour cream and refrigerate.

title: swiss corn bake
directions: Combine the corn, milk, egg, onion, salt, pepper and 3/4 of the shredded Swiss cheese in a greased baking dish.
Top with the remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Blend shortening, sugar and egg until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk or juice to creamed mixture. Beat until smooth.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter in bottom of pan. Add brown sugar; blend thoroughly and spread evenly in bottom of pan.
Arrange pineapple slices over surface of mixture.
Pour batter on top.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
In a casserole, slice potatoes and onion.
Add mixed vegetables and hamburger.
Top with mushrooms and tomato soup.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple ham
directions: In a slow cooker, pour one can pineapple juice; add 1/2 of an unsliced ham, just a pinch of salt and pepper.
It's best to start this in the morning and let cook in slow cooker all day.
Will be ready for supper.
Must cook for several hours.
Great for Thanksgiving or Christmas.

title: chicken curry
directions: Skin and cut the chicken to required pieces then wash.	Add the oil to a pan and warm the oils, then add the onions, curry leaves, cinnamon, garlic, and ginger.
Fry till all turn golden brown or about 7 minutes. Add the chicken pieces and the rest of ingredients, except the coconut milk.
Stir well and let it fry on a low fire for about 10 minutes stirring often.
Then add the coconut milk and 1 cup of water and let it cook on medium fire for about 15 minutes.

title: play dough(kids recipe)
directions: Stir all ingredients over low heat in saucepan.
When it pulls from edges, remove and knead until cool.
Store in sealed bags for up to 3 months.
Add food coloring for desired colors.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Mix sugar and Karo.
Heat to boiling.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips.
Spread over Rice Krispies.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: spinach salad
directions: Remove stems from spinach; wash leaves thoroughly and pat dry. Tear into bite-size pieces.
Combine spinach, mushrooms, eggs and green onions in a large bowl.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook the chicken breasts until done.
Remove the bones and cut the chicken; put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Salt and pepper to taste. In a large mixing bowl mix 1 1/2 cups of the warm chicken broth, drained vegetables, cream of chicken soup and celery soup.
Stir until smooth and pour over the chicken.
In another bowl mix flour, milk and melted margarine.
Pour over mixture.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown at 400°.

title: sweet and saucy franks
directions: Heat equal amounts grape jelly and catsup in saucepan or microwave, uncovered, at High 1 to 2 minutes until mixture can be blended smooth.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, butter, peanut butter, sugars and egg.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Chill dough.
Roll into ball size of large walnuts. Place 3-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour, crisscross.
Bake until set, but not hard at 375°.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen 2 1/2-inch.

title: mom's banana cake
directions: Cream butter flavored Crisco and sugar.
Stir in flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add mashed bananas and 1/3 cup of buttermilk. Beat for 2 minutes.
Then add 1/3 cup buttermilk and 2 eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Stir in 2/3 cup chopped nuts.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch glass pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes (can use aluminum pan).
Check for doneness with toothpick.

title: salmon pie
directions: Cool salmon in the oven about 45 minutes.
Defrost frozen spinach and drain.
Cook white rice.
Mix salmon and rice and add eggs.
Add nutmeg, salt and pepper to taste.
Use already made pie crust (or your own recipe).
Layer spinach and rice mixture.
Use already made croissant dough to cover and decorate the top.
Cover with aluminum foil and cook at 450° for approximately 40 minutes and uncover until croissant gets crispy.

title: baked pineapple chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Combine reserved juice with garlic, cornstarch, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and rosemary. Arrange chicken in shallow baking pan or broilerproof dish, skin side up.
Broil until browned.
Stir sauce; pour over chicken.

title: broccoli cheese dip
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in butter.
Melt cheese in a double boiler.
Add cooked, drained broccoli, mushrooms and onion.
Serve warm.

title: blt dip delight
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sour cream.
Stir into mixture the bacon bits and chopped tomatoes.
Serve with toast (one piece of bread, cut into 4 triangles).

title: pancake burger
directions: Brown beef and onion, drain.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients.
(Tomatoes and corn with their liquid.)
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: christmas ornaments
directions: Mix salt and flour together.
Add water, a little at a time. Roll dough to 1/4-inch thick and cut with a cookie cutter.
Use a nail to make a hole in top of ornament.
Bake on cookie sheet for 30 minutes at 325°.
Cook until hard.
When cool, varnish to protect from moisture.
Paint or glitter make beautiful ornaments. Put child's age on back. They are a keepsake.

title: lasagne roll-ups
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Add noodles and cook 10-12 minutes.
Rinse under cold water and lay out flat.
Cut noodles in half.
Brown ground beef with onion; drain fat.
Add next seven ingredients mixing thoroughly.
Spread 1/4 c. beef mixture evenly on noodles.
Roll up and place seam side down in 9x13 dish.
Pour sauce over roll ups.
Sprinkle with Parmesan, and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sugar syrup
directions: Bring to a hard boil for 1 minute.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In oil saute broccoli, onion and celery.
Stir in remaining ingredients and allow to cook a few minutes.
Pour into greased dish and bake, covered, at 325°
to 350° for about 45 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix dressing ingredients together and refrigerate; pour over salad before serving.

title: mayonnaise muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Spoon into a greased muffin pan. Bake 10 minutes at 425°. Makes 6 muffins.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in order given in 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Chill overnight to blend flavors.

title: better-than-sex cake
directions: In a mixer bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix, oil and water. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in sour cream, grated chocolate, chocolate chips, pecans and coconut. Turn batter into a well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Serves 12 to 16. Sprinkle confectioners sugar on top or frost, if desired.
Really rich!

title: millionaire salad
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended. Pour into mold and place in refrigerator to set (about 1 hour). Slice and serve on lettuce leaves and dot with mayonnaise and a nut on top to decorate. For a dessert, top with whipped cream instead of mayonnaise. Serves 6.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Crush wafers.
Mix all fruit and wafers.
Add milk and mix well.
Press into tube pan. Leave all night.

title: quick chow chow
directions: Drain corn and beans.
Pour all together in a large bowl.
Add chopped cabbage and mix well.
Salt to taste.
Cover tightly, being sure fluid covers veggies.
Let set out in a warm place until it starts to sour.
Then refrigerate until all is used.
Fry as much as is needed in bacon drippings.

title: saloma
directions: Blend together.
Mix; make 2 (1 pound) rolls.
Wrap in foil and put in icebox for 24 hours.
Punch holes in bottom of rolls. Put on cookie rack over pan with water in it.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: hamburger sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together; mix well.
Form into long rolls, approximately 1 1/2 to 2-inches.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Place in freezer for 24 hours.
Remove plastic wrap and place on baking sheet.
Should be very little drippings.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
I turn oven up to 450° for an added 10 minutes.

title: pecan cake with praline glaze
directions: Combine
raisins
and bourbon, stirring well.
Cover and refrigerate
at
least
hour.
Cream
butter;
gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each
addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and nutmeg; add
to creamed
mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending
with
flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition. Fold in pecans and reserved raisin mixture.
Pour batter into a greased and
floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until
wooden
pick
inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan
minutes;
remove to wire rack, and drizzle Praline Glaze over cake.
Cool completely.

title: perfection salad
directions: Add pineapple, cabbage and carrots to slightly thickened jello.
Chill until firm.
Serve with a dollop of mayonnaise.

title: smokies
directions: Combine wieners, jelly and sauce.
Cook in crock-pot approximately 1 hour.

title: spinach salad
directions: Clean spinach and tear into bite size pieces. Add bacon, eggs, onion and mushrooms.
Set aside.
Put remaining ingredients into a blender and blend to make the dressing.
When ready to serve, pour dressing over salad.

title: stroganoff
directions: Combine all 4 ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Add mushrooms about 15 minutes before serving. Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: vegetable stew
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
Add onion, bell pepper, garlic and celery; saute a few minutes.
Add rest of the ingredients and cook over low heat for about 30 minutes.
Cook in a 4-quart cooker with tight lid.

title: golden carrots
directions: Cook carrots covered in boiling salted water until tender, about 20 minutes; drain.
Meanwhile, combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and ground ginger in small saucepan.
Add orange juice; cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in margarine.
Pour over hot carrots, tossing to coat evenly.
Serves 4.

title: spaghetti beef casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling, salted water until barely tender; drain.
Using a heavy kettle with a tight fitting cover, saute onion in butter until lightly browned.
Add ground beef and brown until meat is crumbly.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in soup and water.
Add mushrooms, 2/3 of the cheese, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix in the cooked spaghetti.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Turn into a lightly greased casserole. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Beat until creamy the sugar, flour, butter, egg yolks and salt.
Add lemon juice and rind and milk.
Whip well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into the lemon mixture.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.

title: ritz cracker pudding
directions: Mix together and pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with Dream Whip if desired.

title: brownie bottom pie
directions: Bake brownie mix according to package directions. Let cool. Mix according to package directions. Beat with wire whisk one minute. Let stand for two minutes. Spread over brownies. Top with Cool whip. Garnish with grated chocolate.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and chill for 45 minutes.
Serve with raw vegetables or chips.

title: christmas cranberry salad
directions: Cook the cranberries in 3/4 cup water a few minutes, until tender.
While still hot, dissolve the gelatin and sugar in this mixture.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add the grapes, celery, undrained crushed pineapple and nuts.
Chill in a 1 1/2 qt. ring mold. Serve with Snowy Dressing.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and shrimp.
Pat into a ball.
Refrigerate overnight.
Prior to serving, prepare sauce.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter. Add eggs. Beat well and add bananas.
Mix milk, water and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with flour and salt. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Ice the cake while it is still warm.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; add remaining ingredients to pan. Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes covered and 30 minutes more uncovered.
Sprinkle with chinese noodles and set back into oven for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: yankee beans
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon together and drain.
Add onion, celery, ketchup, and small amount of water and simmer for 20 minutes.
While simmering put beans, vinegar, mustard, sugar and salt in crock pot.
After simmering meat sauce pour over beans and mix well.
Add enough water to make soupy but not runny.
Cook in crock pot until warm and bubbly.

title: spring lawn treatment
directions: Mix ingredients; place in hose applicator jar.
Sprays 2,500 square foot lawn.

title: veal parmigiana
directions: Pound the veal cutlets very thin.
Cook the tomato sauce, onion and basil over low heat for 15 minutes.
Taste for seasoning.
Beat the egg, salt and pepper together in a flat dish. Mix bread crumbs and cheese on a piece of wax paper.
Dip the veal cutlets first in the egg mixture and then in the cheese mixture.
Heat the olive oil in a skillet and brown the veal on both sides.
Transfer to a baking pan and cover with the tomato sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven 15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: easy and delicious duck
directions: Place duck
on large piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil. Combine sherry,
onion
soup mix and mushroom soup.
Pour over duck.
Sprinkle
with
seasoning
salt
to taste.
Close foil, making a tent 2-inches above the duck breast.
Place in baking dish, preferably on a rack.
Do not cover.	Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
The stock
makes
excellent
gravy.
Do
not cook more than 1 duck in
a
tent.
If ducks are smaller than a mallard, reduce ingredients proportionately.

title: plain tomato sauce(salsa di pomodoro semplice)
directions: This recipe for
plain
sauce
is
used
for
making
a variety of dishes including:
baked macaroni, lasagne, zucchini parmesans and a starting base for many of my other recipes.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: In saucepan, bring sugar, cocoa, margarine, milk and salt to a rapid boil for 1 minute. Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla and mix well. Quickly drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper and let cool. Makes 24 servings.

title: shrimp rice
directions: Steam rice. Cook bacon in microwave until crispy. Put oleo and drippings from bacon in large pot. Saute onion in drippings, then add shrimp and cook until done. Add rice,
Worcestershire sauce and bacon (all crushed up) together. Salt rice before cooking and add pepper while stirring all together.

title: fried cabbage and noodles(hulshki)
directions: Chop cabbage into bite size pieces.
Fry in butter until soft. Boil noodles according to directions on package.
Mix cabbage and noodles.
Serve warm.

title: chocolate oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk, butter, vanilla and salt.
Let come to a rolling boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal and peanut butter, stirring well.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper and let cool.
Serve.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and cool. In skillet, melt butter and saute onions and green peppers until tender.
Add meat and brown slowly; then set aside.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix cake mix and pudding mix.
Add 7-Up and oil.
Beat eggs and add to cake mixture.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pinto beans and neck bone
directions: Cook down to a gravy.

title: country ham with red-eye gravy
directions: Make cuts in fat to keep ham from curling.
Melt butter over low heat in a heavy skillet.
Add ham and cook 5 minutes on each side until light brown.
Remove from skillet and keep warm.
Stir brown sugar into hot drippings until dissolved, if brown sugar is desired.
Add coffee; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.

title: pineapple millionaire pie
directions: Cream together powdered sugar and butter on electric mixer. Add eggs, salt and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Spread mixture evenly into baked pie crust, then chill.
Whip cream until stiff.
Blend in powdered sugar.
Fold in pineapple and pecans. Spread this mixture on top of base mixture and chill thoroughly. Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: chocolate-pecan brownies
directions: Set oven to 325°. In small bowl, mix flour and baking soda. In a small saucepan, combine sugar, butter and water; bring to the boil over medium heat. Remove from heat. Stir in 1 cup of morsels and the vanilla until smooth. Transfer mixture to a medium bowl and cool completely. Stir in eggs one at a time, beating well. Gradually stir in flour mixture until smooth. Stir in remaining morsels and nuts. Pour batter into a greased 9-inch square baking pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until a pick inserted in middle comes out clean. Cool and cut into squares. Makes 16 brownies.

title: "snowflakes"(cookies)
directions: Cream shortening and cheese well.
Add sugar gradually and continue creaming.
Beat in yolk, vanilla and orange rind.
Sift flour, salt and cinnamon.
Add to mixture.
Fill cookie press. Form cookie on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Skin chicken; cut from bones into 1-inch cubes.
Combine sauce: water, soy sauce, honey, vinegar and cornstarch.
Blend; set aside. Preheat wok at 325° for 2 minutes.
Add oil.
Add chicken; stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Add peppers and cashews.
Stir 1/2 minute.
Add onions, garlic, ginger and crushed pepper.
Fry 1 minute.
Add sauce without stirring 1 minute, then stir 1 minute.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: thai egg rolls
directions: Beat 1 egg in small bowl and set aside (this will be used to roll the wrappers). Combine the rest of the above ingredients, mixing well (this is the stuffing in your egg rolls, make sure all ingredients are evenly mixed).

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix together and bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
You may use a tube pan, 2 larger loaf pans or 3 medium loaf pans. Baking time will be less for smaller pans.

title: peanut butter snack mix
directions: In a measuring cup, combine peanut butter, butter and spices. Microwave on High 1 minute or until butter melts.
Mix well.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, combine popcorn, shredded wheat and pretzels.
Pour peanut butter mixture over popcorn mixture.
Toss until well coated.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes stirring halfway through cooking time.
Cool popcorn mixture to room temperature. Stir in candy pieces.
Makes 8 cups.
One cup: 302 calories, 7 grams protein, 34 grams carbohydrates, 16 grams fat, 119 grams sodium, 8 miligrams cholesterol.

title: poor boy cake
directions: Mix ingredients together by hand in a large bowl, 2 ingredients at a time, until all are blended well.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until done in center.
Frost with favorite icing and enjoy.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Place in 2 cups warm water and stir until dissolved.
Melt butter; cream sugar and butter in large mixing bowl, then add beaten egg.
Add dissolved yeast to creamed mixture.
Add flour and stir by hand until well mixed and smooth.
Place in airtight container and refrigerate.
Keeps for several days using as needed. Stir well before each use.
To bake, drop by spoonfuls into well-greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350°.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Whisk egg yolks, water and lemon juice together in a small saucepan.

Cook and stir over low heat until mixture bubbles around the edges, about 20 minutes. add cold butter chunks to mixture one at a time, whisking after each addition until butter is incorporated into mixture.
Stir in seasonings.
Serve immediately. Yield:
1 cup.

title: my crazy meat loaf
directions: Mix together and put on top of meat loaf or whatever other meat you wish.

title: deep fried squash
directions: Slice squash and dip in milk.
Put the flour and squash in a plastic bag and shake to coat slices.
Drop slices in hot oil of a deep fryer.
Fry until lightly browned.
After they are taken out of deep fryer, sprinkle with a little sugar.

title: fried pie dough
directions: Add all dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until size of small peas.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Chill before rolling for pies.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes with 1/2 cup melted butter in a large bowl. Add salt, pepper, onion, cream of chicken soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Cover with corn flakes mixed with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: northwest apple crumb pie
directions: Combine 1/4 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and cinnamon.
Mix well with apples and raisins.
Pile into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup flour and 1/4 cup sugar.
Mix in margarine until mixture is crumbly. Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Bake 25 minutes longer (if necessary, cover loosely with aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning).
Drizzle confectioners sugar frosting over warm pie.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together and bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Add dry ingredients (flour, soda and salt), mixing until well blended.
Add filling and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 5 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
This recipe makes 3 loaves.
Ice bread with thin icing.
Place nuts or dried apricot pieces across top.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding mix well.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: fudge pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and melt margarine.
Thoroughly mix all ingredients and pour into an uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until firm.
Do not overcook.

title: broccoli-corn bake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, margarine, onion flakes and pepper. Combine broccoli, egg and corn.
Add the cracker mixture to the broccoli, saving 1/4 cup cracker crumbs to sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Saute in 1/2 stick margarine, onions (chopped) and cubed zucchini.
Melt 1 stick margarine with the box stuffing.
Mix cream of chicken soup, sour cream and grated carrots together. Layer zucchini-onion mixture and next stuffing mix.
Then layer soup mix.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: canned green beans
directions: Cover beans with water and boil 30 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Butter a 9 1/2-inch pie plate.
Spread apples in pan.
Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Cream butter and add sugar; cream until light.
Beat in egg.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder. Add to butter, sugar and egg mixture.
Spoon batter over apples. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: macaroni mousse
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain. Combine with next five ingredients.
Place into baking dish that has been oiled or sprayed with Pam.
Add milk to beaten eggs and pour over top of casserole.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix jello and water; dissolve.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add cherry and pineapple and pour 1/2 in pan and let chill.
Mix cream cheese with milk and spread over jello.
Sprinkle nuts on cheese. Add remaining jello.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: instant "homemade" soup
directions: Adjust number of cans for quantity needed.

title: spiced chicken with fruit
directions: Heat oil in skillet until hot. Mix salt and red pepper. Sprinkle on chicken. Cook chicken in oil over medium heat 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown. Stir in remaining ingredients, except orange sections and parsley. Heat until boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until juices of chicken run clear. Garnish with orange sections and parsley.

title: chicken curry salad
directions: In a large bowl combine first 7 ingredients. Blend together the mayonnaise and curry powder and pour over previous mixture, stir until evenly distributed.

title: chinese chews
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar, flour, salt and baking powder. Mix until crumbly.
Add eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread in greased and floured 14 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.

title: coconut dream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix with 1 cup milk as directed on package using large mixer bowl.
Add remaining milk and the pie filling mix.
Blend, then beat at high speed for 2 minutes scraping bowl occasionally.
Fold in coconut.
Spoon into crust. Chill at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: brenda's no bake cookies
directions: Boil together sugar, butter, milk and cocoa for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, oats and vanilla. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cook and then enjoy!

title: cowboy beans
directions: Drain and remove pork from all beans.
Pour lean of beans and sprinkle diced onions on top.
Pour on next can; sprinkle onions on top.
Repeat until all beans have been used.
Pour browned hamburger on top.
Use approximately 1 1/2 pound pork and 1/2 bottle Bull's-Eye barbecue sauce on top of hamburger.
Cook in crock-pot on high for 2 1/2 hours.
Then stir and simmer for one more hour in crock.

title: chicken or tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.

title: venison ragout
directions: Saute the venison in butter, add 1/4 cup wine and water. Simmer until meat is tender.
Add onion and mushrooms and braise for another 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in garlic, tomato, salt, pepper, thyme, bay leaf, remaining wine and orange juice.
Simmer 10 minutes more.
If ragout needs thickening, make a paste of flour and water; cook until thick.
Serves 4.

title: williamsburg cream of peanut soup
directions: Saute celery and onions in butter until soft and brown.
Add flour, blending well.
Add chicken stock, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and puree in a food processor. Add peanut butter and cream.
Stir thoroughly.
Return to low heat; do not boil.
Garnish with chopped peanuts.

title: no bake oatmeal chocolate cookies
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients, working rapidly; mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto buttered pan or wax paper
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a medium bowl combine peanut butter and Rice Krispies until well blended.
Press into pie plate.
This is the crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Pour into shell.
Slice banana on top of this; top with Cool Whip.

title: rolls
directions: Mix potatoes, Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Beat real good. Add 2 cups flour and half of the milk and yeast; beat again.
Add rest of milk, yeast and flour; beat again. With hands, work about 1 to 2 cups flour into dough or until not sticky.
Roll and cut out like biscuits. Bake what you need. Place the rest in a bowl. Cover and put in refrigerator.
Will keep for about 1 week.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large mixing bowl, combine cereal and boiling water.
Stir in oil and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients until well mixed.
Spoon into desired number of greased muffin cups, filling 3/4 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until tops spring back when lightly touched.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Melt margarine and brown sugar.
Add pretzels and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes.
Cream 10x sugar and cream cheese together.
Add whipped topping and mix well. Spread over cooled pretzels.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water and add frozen strawberries.
Stir until strawberries are separated.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook slowly until thick, about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir frequently to prevent sticking.
Pour into hot jars, leaving 1 inch headspace.
Pressure cook at 10 pounds pressure for 25 minutes.

title: chicken croissants
directions: Boil chicken breasts until they are completely done. Chop into small pieces. Add cream of mushroom soup, salt, pepper, mayonnaise, cheese and egg in medium size bowl. Mix well.

title: pickled onion and cucumber slices
