directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Heat to dissolve sugar. Alternate layers of cucumbers and onion in bowl.
Cover vinegar mixture over vegetables and cover.
Refrigerate several hours. Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix beans, sugar, mustard and chopped onion together in a casserole
dish.
Place bacon slices on top of bean mixture. Cover with
foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered, and 20 more minutes, uncovered.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In large boiler over medium heat, combine 1 1/2 cups sweet milk, evaporated milk, egg yolks, sugar, salt and oleo (reserve 1/2 cup sweet milk).
Bring to boil.
In cup mix 1/2 cup milk with cornstarch; add to other mixture and cook until quite thick.
Stir in vanilla and 1 package flaked coconut.
Pour in baked pie shell. Chill before serving.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 pan with Pam. Layer graham crackers on the bottom, breaking to form one layer. Mix with mixer all pkg of vanilla pudding with 6 cups skim milk, until thick. Fold in cool whip. Pour half of this over graham crackers.

title: dessert fondue
directions: Heat the first 3 ingredients over low heat or heat in a fondue or crock-pot until chocolate melts.
Use meat skewers or forks to dip the cake or fruit into the chocolate.
Eat one piece at a time immediately after dipping it into the chocolate.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Mix all ingredients together; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in casserole; sprinkle paprika on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped eggplant (casserole)
directions: Boil eggplant until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add margarine; set aside.
Beat eggs and combine with remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Mix in eggplant and pour mixture into a buttered baking dish.
Cover top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables. Bring vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper to a boil.
Let cool and pour over vegetables.
Set overnight.
Keeps 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain.
Cover with cold water and parboil them until skins burst.
Place salt pork and onion in bottom of pot.
Add beans and other ingredients.
Cover with water.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, then at 325° for 5 hours.

title: sausage and cheese surprise
directions: Place bread in 8 x 12-inch pan.
Top with grated cheese.
Brown sausage, cut into thirds and place on top of cheese.
Beat eggs with 2 1/2 cups milk and dry mustard.
Pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: millionaire's pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually add sugar.
Mix cracker crumbs and nuts and fold into egg whites.
Spread in 9-inch ungreased pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°; cool.

title: jiffy cake mix dessert
directions: Separate eggs.	Put yolks into a measuring cup.
Add water to 1/2 mark plus add 2 tablespoons.
Beat cake mix and yolk mixture together for 2 minutes.
Place in a 9 x 13 pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add sugar until peaks form.
Spread egg whites on top of the cake mixture.	Sprinkle nuts over the egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Spread Cool Whip over the top and arrange pie filling over the topping. Chill until serving.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Beat eggs and Bisquick, oil and cheese.
Fold in zucchini. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add cooked broccoli, rice, soup, water, milk and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Run cold water through them and let them drain.
This keeps them from sticking together.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve 1 cup sugar and 1 cup hot water.
Dissolve the jello (flavor of your choice).
I use color I want in 2 cups boiling water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add the ginger ale before serving.

title: pork chop-n-potato bake
directions: Brown chops in lightly greased skillet.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt; set aside.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream and 1/2 can fried onion rings.
Spoon mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Arrange chops over hash browns.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and add onion and garlic; cook until onion is limp, then add the canned ingredients.
In a large, shallow dish, alternate the meat, tortillas and cheese in that order.
Bake at 325° to 350° until bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: chocolate peanut delight
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, milk and egg in a bowl.
Add 3/4 c of peanuts.
Spread into greased 13x9 inch pan.

title: german pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place margarine in 10-inch cast-iron skillet or tin pie plate and allow margarine to melt.

title: harvest hamburger casserole
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine beef, onion, tomatoes with liquid, Worcestershire sauce and salt. Spoon into a greased 3-quart casserole. Layer the potatoes, flour, corn and green pepper on top. Bake, covered, at 375° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with the cheese and continue baking, uncovered, for about 10 minutes. Yield: 8 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: In a large bowl, empty cake mix, jello and oil.
Mix.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating slowly after each one.
Fold in strawberries.
Pour batter into three 8-inch layer pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 or 35 minutes.

title: cheddar-baked zucchini and turkey ham
directions: Put a layer of zucchini in the bottom of a baking dish.
Add a layer of cheese, a layer of tomatoes and a layer of ham.
Continue layering until ingredients are gone, then sprinkle with crumbs. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes until tender, brown and bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Blend shortening and sugar together.
Add tomato soup and soda.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to the first mixture. Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into loaf or tube pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip; add lemon juice, blueberries and nuts.
Pour into 2 graham cracker pie shells. Chill overnight.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter (1/4 cup) in microwave.
Beat eggs. Stir all ingredients together and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
(Center will be last to cook so check that center is firm.)
Makes 1 pie.

title: cheese stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse and pat dry mushrooms and remove stems.
Set caps aside for stuffing.
In medium bowl beat cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, paprika, onion powder and nutmeg until well blended.
Stir in celery.
Spoon into reserved mushroom caps.
Sprinkle with paprika. Broil at 500° until cheese browns.
Serve warm.

title: potluck vegetable casserole
directions: Drain whole corn.
Add vegetables and mushrooms.
Combine the cream-style corn, cheese and soup.
Fold in drained vegetables. Turn into a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Melt butter; toss with crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Stir together first 4 ingredients; press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk, then melted peanut butter chips until mixture is smooth.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat well.
Stir in mini chocolate chips and pour over crust.
Bake until center is soft (approximately 55 to 65 minutes).
Cool.
Cover and refrigerate.
Can be garnished by drizzling melted chocolate over top.

title: apple roly poly
directions: Peel, core and finely chop apples.
Prepare biscuit mix as directed on package.

On lightly floured board, roll dough into oblong (approximately 10 x 12-inches), about 1/4-inch thick. Spread with honey to within 1-inch of the edges of the dough. Combine the spices and sugar; toss with apples.
Spread apples evenly over the honey.
Dot apples with butter.
Fold up like a jellyroll; seal well.
Bake in a greased pan with sides, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Slice and serve hot with whipped cream.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: You need a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Wash, clean and dice rhubarb; let drain.
Prepare cake mix per directions on box.
Grease bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Layer diced rhubarb, sprinkle sugar and strawberry Jell-O on top.
Layer miniature marshmallows over that.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush cookies.
Put 1/2 on bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix margarine and cream cheese until smooth, then add powdered sugar. Fold in Cool Whip.
In separate bowl, put pudding mix, milk and vanilla.
Mix. Add to cream cheese mixture and mix well about 5 minutes with mixer.
Spread on top of cookie crumbs.
Put remaining cookie crumbs on top and refrigerate.

title: vegetable-cheese chowder
directions: Bring water to a boil in a large saucepan over high heat.
Add potatoes, leeks, celery (and 1 teaspoon salt, optional).
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes.
Melt butter in medium saucepan over medium-low heat.
Remove from heat and blend in flour. Add milk, Worcestershire sauce (remaining salt, optional), mustard and pepper.
Return to medium-low heat and stir until thickened, about 10 minutes. Stir into potato mixture. Add tomatoes, Parmesan and parsley.
Ladle soup into heated bowls and serve. Serves 6.

title: chocolate mint cookies
directions: Cook butter, sugar and water until butter is melted.
Add chocolate pieces; stir until melted.
Pour into large mixing bowl; let stand 10 minutes.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill dough 1 hour for easier handling.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Roll a teaspoon of dough into a ball.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 13 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately place a mint on each cookie.
Allow to soften, then swirl!
Makes approximately 60 cookies.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, mustard and salt.
Sprinkle one side of beef boneless round steak with half of the flour mixture; pound in. Turn beef and pound in remaining flour mixture.
Cut beef into 6 serving pieces.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet until hot.
Cook beef in oil over medium heat, turning once, until brown, about 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes and garlic; break up tomatoes.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beef is tender, about 1 1/4 hours.
Add water, onion and green pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, 5 to 8 minutes.
Makes 6 servings; 270 calories per serving.

title: potato cheese hurry-up(for microwave)
directions: Cook on High in microwave; stir after 15 minutes. Cook a total of 9 to 11 minutes. After cooked, sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour until combined.
Add cream and 1 1/2 cups of the broth all at once; stir until smooth.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from the heat; add the cheese and stir until melted.
Stir in macaroni, chicken, pimientos, salt and pepper.
Add additional broth if needed.
Pour into a 3-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Process until smooth. Chill.
Use for chilled soups or potatoes.

title: mom's applesauce cake
directions: Cream in mixer, shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and applesauce.
Sift together flour, salt and soda. Mix dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Add raisins or raisins and dates.
Add walnuts.
Dump into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then "eject" letting sit on cake rack at least 30 minutes before cutting and preferably until loaf is cool.
(Drape with clean tea towel.)

title: pizza sauce with pizza dough recipe
directions: Mix sausage and tomato sauce together and place over pizza dough.
To each pizza, add oregano, garlic salt and pinch of red pepper.
Mix 2 pounds Mozzarella cheese.
Put 2 tablespoons olive oil on top of pizza.

title: hot tea or russian
directions: Mix together; store in airtight container.
To use, add 2 heaping teaspoons per cup of boiling water.
May be made in cup or the equivalent to make a pot of tea.

title: pistachio - angel food cake
directions: Slit cake into 2 or 3 layers.
Spread layers, top and sides, with mixture.
Let set 1 hour.

title: canned fruit cake
directions: Do not grease pan.
Put drained fruit in pan.
Sprinkle nutmeg, then Jiffy cake mix, then nutmeg and juice.
Then butter with 1/2 stick butter.
Bake in 350° oven until nicely browned.

title: rice salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Let stand about 30 minutes to allow flavors to blend.
Add remaining ingredients and toss gently.

title: fish vera cruz
directions: Marinate fish in lime juice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Turn a couple of times.
Remove, pat dry.
Brown in olive oil.
Remove from pan.
Add to pan, onions and garlic; fry until brown.
Add tomato puree, water, olives, capers and chilli peppers and cook covered for 10 minutes.
Add fish and spoon sauce over it.
Cook 7 to 10 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: chicken pot pie #2
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in casserole dish in the order listed.
Combine milk, butter and flour.
Pour over mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey glazed chicken
directions: In a bowl or bag, combine flour, salt, cayenne or paprika. Add chicken pieces; shake to coat.
Pour 4 tablespoons butter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken in pan, turning once to coat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Combine the last 5 ingredients with remaining butter; pour over chicken.
Bake 45 minutes more, or until chicken is tender, basting several times with pan drippings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly. Pour into 9 x 13 greased baking pan, then put topping over cake.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook the broccoli and onion in water until tender.
Drain. Puree in blender.
Add chicken broth and pour into a boiler.
Melt oleo.
Add flour and salt.
When it thickens, add half and half milk.
Pour into the broccoli puree and heat.
Do not boil. Serves six.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done; cut chicken into small pieces. Mix chicken soup, mushroom soup and sour cream together. Add chicken to mixture and pour into casserole dish. Top with crumbled crackers; pour melted butter over crackers. Bake for approximately 30 minutes in a 350° preheated oven.

title: sourdough bread
directions: In a large nonmetal bowl, dissolve yeast in 2 cups of water (105° to 115°).
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add 3 1/2 cups flour and 1 tablespoon of sugar and blend well.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap and a cloth towel.
Let stand in warm place (80° to 85°) for five days, stirring at least once each day.
When the Starter is ready for use, it is bubbly and may have a yellow liquid on top. Stir well before using.

title: cinnamon - raisin muffins
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, cereal, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder and cinnamon; set aside.
In small bowl, combine milk, egg, margarine and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Stir in raisins.
Spoon mixture evenly into 12 greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan.
Brush tops of muffins with fruit juice and roll in remaining sugar.
Serve warm.

title: billee's dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Good on wheat crackers.

title: yellow rice and corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
While it is warm, add margarine, corn, and soup.
Grate cheese and stir in part of cheese in casserole.
Top with remainder.
Cook about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: rolled sugar cookieseverton, missouri
directions: Cream butter, vanilla and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat eggs with milk and stir into creamed mixture.

title: florida fudge
directions: Mix together in rather large pan sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil slowly and at full boil cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Have ready in a large bowl, chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
Stir cooked mixture into chips and marshmallow cream. Stir until chips melt also add; butter, nuts, and vanilla.
Stir until mixture cools and begins to thicken.
Pour into buttered jelly roll pan.
Cut when cold.
Let stand 24 hours, turn after 12 hours.
Yield:
5 pounds.

title: ron gilbert's flank steak
directions: Tenderize a flank steak.
Make marinade from remaining ingredients.
Marinate flank steak in closed container overnight. Turn once or twice.
Broil several inches from broiler, 4 minutes on each side or grill on outside grill.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a casserole dish. You may crush saltine crackers over top.
Bake at 350° uncovered, until bubbly and lightly browned.

title: banata spinach bread
directions: Take sausage out of casing.
Fry sausage, garlic and onion until cooked.
Boil spinach; drain.
Add to sausage and saute 15 minutes.
Add Mozzarella cheese and melt.
Slice bread in 1/2 lengthwise; scoop out middle.
Place sausage mixture in scooped out bread halves.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Put halves together.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Slice in pieces and serve.

title: crock-pot pork chops
directions: Place uncooked, seasoned pork chops in crock-pot.
Pour a little barbecue sauce on each piece.
Add no water.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 9 hours.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sour cream.
Pour half in a long flat dish; congeal, then spread sour cream over this.
Add remaining 1/2 of mixture and congeal.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Boil together the water, vinegar, sugar and salt. Cut cucumbers in quarters.
Put cucumbers, garlic and dill in a gallon jar. Add liquid.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chuck roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place meat in the center of a large piece heavy-duty Reynolds Wrap; place in a roasting pan.
Brush meat with A.1. sauce; sprinkle onion soup mix over it.
Spread with mushroom soup.
Wrap loosely in foil and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: banana quick bread
directions: Blend shortening, salt and sugar.
Add eggs, sifted flour, soda, banana pulp and crushed pecans.
Bake in a well greased loaf pan in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: spaghetti sauce starter
directions: Cut up peeled tomatoes into quarters.
Chop bell peppers, onions and hot peppers.
In a large stewing pot, bring all ingredients to boil, then cook slowly for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
The sauce may be canned or let sauce cool and then freeze.

title: nutty yams
directions: Boil yams until soft.
Peel, cool and mash in mixer.
Blend in vanilla and sugar (to taste).
Chop and blend in pecans.
(No added liquid needed; freezing does not impair quality.)

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Stir in brown sugar and barbecue sauce.
Grease muffin tin.
Place biscuits in tin and form a cup.
Spoon mixture in biscuit cup and top with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Grease and flour 9-inch x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 of cake batter into pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
While cake is cooking, melt butter, milk and candy over low heat.
Remove cake from oven and pour melted candy mixture over cake.
Sprinkle nuts, chocolate chips, and remaining batter on top.
Bake for an additional 20 to 25 minutes.

title: simple steak
directions: *I don't use any.
I find the salt in the soup is plenty.

title: party squash casserole
directions: Cook squash 8 or 10 minutes; drain.
Place squash in large bowl and mash.
Stir in mayonnaise and next 8 ingredients.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: italian cheese twists
directions: On lightly floured surface, roll dough out into 12-inch square. Combine butter and seasoning; spread over dough.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Fold dough into thirds.
Cut crosswise into 24 strips (1/2 inch strips).
Twist each strip twice and pinch ends together.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Cover, allow to raise until almost double, about 30 minutes.
In a small bowl beat egg and water together.
Brush on rolls.
Sprinkle with cheese and/or sesame seed.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until done.

title: easter bread
directions: Put yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Heat milk with sugar, shortening and salt; cool to warm.
Stir in 1 cup flour until smooth.
Add yeast mixture and egg; add flavoring, if desired.
Add enough flour to make a smooth dough.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, flip over and let rise for 45 to 50 minutes. Punch down.
Make 1/3 of dough into 6 egg shapes; place together on a greased baking pan.
Shape remaining dough into 2 (26 inch) ropes.
Twist and coil around the eggs.
Let rise for 50 to 55 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and decorate. Happy Easter!

title: mrs. elinor's jam bars
directions: Combine cake mix, oats, margarine and water.
Mix until crumbly in texture.
Spread 1/2 of this mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and pour the jam over top.
Pour remainder of cake crumbs on top of the jam and bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool, cut and serve!

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients to form a very sticky dough. Knead in additional flour as needed. Roll or pat out circles of dough 1/4-inch thick and about 6-inches wide. Heat oil until hot. Fry quickly, turning once. Serves 6 to 8.

title: broiled grapefruit
directions: Cut grapefruit in half and remove seeds and center.
Separate the sections.
Sprinkle the grapefruit with cinnamon and brown sugar and dot with butter.
Broil until the grapefruit pulp is hot and the sugar begins to caramelize.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown beef; cook or steam zucchini until tender.
Pour browned beef alternately with layers of cooked zucchini and cheese in an 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Mix the soup and milk together.
Pour over the meat, zucchini and cheese layered in the pan.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned on top.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cheese and sugar.
Add salt and vanilla.
Add eggs and stir in flour.
Spoon into a greased tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions or until tender.
Drain well.
Add salad dressing.
Mix well.
Add all other ingredients. Mix well.
Chill in refrigerator 2 hours before serving.

title: microwave fudge and *truffles
directions: In a 1 1/2 quart casserole, combine all ingredients except butter and pecans.
Stir thoroughly.
Drizzle melted butter on top and microwave on high for 3 minutes.
Add pecans and stir until smooth.
Pour into wax paper - lined pan (8 X 4 X3 inch).
Spread and chill for 1 hour before slicing.

title: cracklin cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour
batter into a well-greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: blueberry buttermilk muffins
directions: In small bowl, combine buttermilk, butter and eggs until blended.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make well in center.
Add buttermilk mixture, stirring until flour mixture is just moistened.
Fold in blueberries. Spoon batter into greased muffin cups, filling 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated 400° oven 20 minutes or until tops are golden and wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan.
Serve warm or cool on wire rack.
Makes about 18 muffins.

title: chocolate chip-banana bread
directions: Spray 2 loaf pans with nonstick vegetable spray.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter or margarine and sugar in a large bowl of electric mixer until creamy.
Add milk, bananas, eggs and vanilla; mix until blended.
In a separate bowl, combine the flour, salt, baking soda; stir to combine all dry ingredients and add to butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool.
Makes 20 to 24 slices.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and butter.
Add juice from oranges and beat until fluffy.
Add oranges, beat well.
Spread batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Frost with Pineapple Frosting.

title: sweet potato oven fries
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Wash potatoes and cut lengthwise into slices no thicker than 1/2 inch. Mix oil, paprika and cumin. Toss potatoes and oil mixture until well coated. Arrange potatoes in single layer on baking sheet sprayed with cooking spray. Bake 45-60 minutes, stirring occasionally, until crisp.

title: sweet-n-sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender and drain.
Mix other ingredients and cook until onions and peppers are soft and mixture begins to thicken.
Pour over carrots.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: dessert cake
directions: Bread up the angel food cake into bite size pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix the jello according to the package instructions and pour over the cake pieces.
Refrigerate until set. Layer strawberries over cake/jello mixture.
Prepare the pudding/pie filling according to package instructions and pour over strawberries.
Add a layer of crushed pineapple.
Cover with a layer of Cool Whip.
Garnish as you like and chill about 4 hours.

title: cheese dip or vegetable sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in double boiler.
Cook over boiling water until custard consistency.
Refrigerate for dip, or use as topping over hot vegetables.
Very nice over cauliflower surrounded by carrots.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 2 layers.
In saucepan, bring 2 cups water and 1 cup sugar to a boil.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup water and add to boiling mix, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Add berries, reserving 4 or 5 berries.
When cake is cool, prepared pudding as directed on package.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Combine ingredients, except taco sauce.
Spread on tortillas. Roll.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with taco sauce.

title: lime-dill fish fillets
directions: Mix all ingredients, except fish, in large bowl.
Add fish. Chill 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until fish is easily flaked with fork.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients to form a ball.
Roll out and cut into squares.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: beet borscht *
directions: Saute onion and celery in 1 tablespoon butter.

Place sauteed onion and celery in large pot with 1 grated beet, garlic, tomatoes with juice, potatoes, stock, water, pepper, parsley and salt. Bring to boil; lower heat immediately and simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Strain out vegetables; puree in food processor and return to soup.
Saute grated beets and carrots in 1 tablespoon butter; add to soup and simmer 15 minutes.
Do not boil, as this will turn red beet color brown.
Saute cabbage in 1 tablespoon or more butter for 5 minutes; add to soup and simmer 15 minutes more. Add lemon juice.
Taste for salt and pepper.
Serve hot with sour cream.

title: quickie egg drop noodles
directions: Bring undiluted soup to a boil.
Beat egg with a fork in a cup.
Add flour (more flour can be added for thicker noodles). Beat, beat, beat.
Add seasoning.
Drop from tip of spoon into bubbling soup.
It's done.
Mmm good!

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add egg, cream again.
Add bananas, flour, salt, soda and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: greek walnut cake
directions: Make syrup before making the cake.
Bring to boil 1 1/4 cups sugar, water and orange flavoring.
Mix well and let cool.

title: spy glass sandwiches
directions: Put all the ingredients for the ham and cheese filling in a small bowl.
Stir and mix everything well.

title: banana rice pudding
directions: Blend bananas to a puree, then mix pineapple, honey and lemon juice.
Add rice.
Fold in whipped cream.
Add raisins and blend. Refrigerate.
Garnish with a slice of banana and whipped cream topped with a dash of cinnamon or walnuts.

title: turkey links
directions: In food processor, combine turkey, onion, egg white, tomato paste and seasonings.
Process until turkey is ground.
Place flour on a piece of wax paper.
Roll sausages lightly in it after link sausages are formed.
To form link sausages, wet hands and form mixture into 8 link shaped sausages, use 1/4 cup for each.
Heat oil in large nonstick frying pan over medium heat.
Add links and sizzle until brownish on all sides and cooked throughout, about 8 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add one egg at a time.
Add 1/2 cup milk and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown beef in oil.
Place in 3-quart casserole and add soup, garlic and wine.
Cover tightly.
Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add mushrooms last 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter, oil and sugars.
Add eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream the margarine; add sugar gradually, beating until there is no trace.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each. Start adding small portions of flour, beating into mixture.
Add sour cream, coconut and flavoring; mix well.
Using a spoon, stir pecans into mixture.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 40 minutes at 325°.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In skillet, brown beef and drain excess oil.
Add 1 cup broth, pepper, bay leaves, cloves and thyme.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add carrots, onions, mushrooms, celery and corn.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: squirrel stew 1
directions: Cut up the squirrels into serving size pieces.
Season with salt and pepper and shake in a paper bag with enough flour to coat squirrels well.
In a large pot, heat vegetable oil and fry squirrels until lightly browned.
Remove them to another container and keep at 150°.
Add flour remaining in bag to the pot and stir while cooking until brown.
Add peppers, onions, celery, parsley, green onions, garlic and squirrels.
Cover with water and add enough Kitchen Bouquet to give stew a nice brown color and toss in 8 or 10 bouillon cubes.
Salt and pepper to taste and add some red pepper, if desired.
Stir well and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for about 5 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: fruit pies
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add 1/4 cup of cherry juice, cherries and pineapple.
Cook until thickens.
Add jello to hot mixture. Cool.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour into crust and chill.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: orange freeze
directions: Combine all ingredients together and mix in blender until ice is dissolved.

title: raisin bread pudding
directions: Place bread cubes in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat together eggs, milk, sugar and vanilla.
Add oranges and pour over bread cubes.
Dab with butter.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Great alone or served with vanilla ice cream.

title: cheese rice
directions: Combine together. Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: bangkok chicken-curry rice(serves 3 to 4)
directions: Sprinkle chicken breast with 2 cloves garlic, soy sauce, sugar, 1/2 teaspoon MSG (optional), parsley to taste and dash of salt and pepper. Marinate 30 minutes.

title: lemon luncheon salad
directions: To 2 cups hot water, add sugar and lemon Jell-O; chill until mixture has set slightly.
Add mayonnaise, Cool Whip, celery, apples and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish; let set until firm.
Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in water; add the ice cubes.
Cool well.
Pour over other mixture; cool several hours until set.
Very colorful; goes well with chicken and pork.

title: fast chicken cordon bleu
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine in frying pan over low to medium heat.
Add crushed garlic.
Add chicken breasts, that have been dipped in eggs and then in bread crumbs until lightly brown on each side.
Remove to baking dish (shallow).
Add cream of mushroom soup to cover breasts.
Top with 1 slice ham and 1 slice of cheese.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serve immediately with rice or potatoes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Place crescent rolls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Mix together and place in a greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: "plum fun" cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well. Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves and beat into ingredients. Stir in 1 cup chopped nuts and bake in greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or less (until done).

title: oriental scallop kabobs
directions: Rinse scallops and place in a bowl with the next 3 ingredients.
Set aside.
Combine oil, lemon juice, parsley, soy sauce and pepper.
Pour sauce over scallop mixture and let stand 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Fry bacon until almost cooked, but not crisp.
Cut each slice into 4 pieces.
Alternate scallops, pineapple, mushrooms, green pepper and bacon on skewers.
May be refrigerated until ready to grill.
Cook over medium hot coals for about 4 or 5 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat sugar and syrup to form smooth syrup.
Remove from fire and stir in butter and Crisco. Add beaten eggs, vanilla and pecans. Stir until eggs are well blended into syrup mixture. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 325° and cook 30 minutes or until filling sets.

title: apple cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix in liquids, then add apples, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: japanese chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add chocolate and melt.
Stir in sugar until well blended.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in coconut and nuts. Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine 1/4 cup of soup with remaining ingredients except water.
Mix thoroughly; shape into 6 patties.
Place in shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Combine remaining soup and water; pour over meat.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: old fashion apple pudding
directions: Place sliced apples in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar, 1/4 cup water and cinnamon.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar with soft butter.
Add and combine remaining ingredients; mix until cake batter consistency.
Pour over apples.
Do not stir.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm with cream or ice cream.
Serves 8.

title: egyptian coconut cake
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter in saucepan.
Heat until butter melts and sugar is dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Bake in a greased 8 1/2 x 13-inch baking pan for 30 minutes.
Serving Size:
Preparation Time:

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a large soup pot. Add chopped onions and cook until soft and translucent. Add flour. Cook another minute. Add chicken stock, broccoli and seasonings.
Bring to a boil. Simmer 20 minutes or until broccoli is tender.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in large heavy saucepan. Add vinegar and water, blending until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sauce comes to boiling.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Add beets and toss well.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Reheat before serving.

title: frozen strawberry daiquiri
directions: Place first 5 ingredients into a container of electric blender; blend to combine.
Add ice cubes, a few at a time, until mixture is slushy.
Pour into freezer container.
Cover and freeze.
Stir occasionally so mixture will not freeze solid.
Garnish with whole strawberry, if desired.
Makes 5 cups.

title: chicken divan
directions: In 10 x 8-inch baking dish, place broccoli, rice and chicken. Mix mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice and curry powder and spread over ingredients in casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove. Spread cheese over top and return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Drizzle sugar and continue beating until real stiff.
Fold in vanilla and salt.
Add chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheets.
Preheat oven to 350°; put in cookies and turn oven off. Eight hours later, cookies will be done.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together into mixing bowl.
Add milk mixed with oil.
Roll dough out on floured board, knead lightly and roll to about 1/2 inch or so.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake 15 minutes in preheated 400 - 450 degree oven.

title: baked cavatelli
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions.
In a large skillet, cook sausage, drain fat and reserve 1 tablespoon.
Cook onion and garlic in the 1 tablespoon fat until tender.

In a 2-quart casserole, combine pasta, sausage, onion, garlic, tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce, 1/2 of the cheese, Italian seasoning and pepper. Stir to combine. Bake, covered, at 375° for 25 minutes. Uncover and sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake 5 minutes more.

title: mccall's microwave chocolate-covered cherries
directions: Line baking sheet with waxed paper.
In small bowl, cream butter, confectioners sugar, milk and almond extract.
(If mixture is too soft, add more sugar.)
On a surface lightly sprinkled with confectioners sugar, knead mixture into a ball.
With fingers, flatten 1 teaspoon dough into a 2-inch round.
With flat metal spatula, lift the round, then mold it around cherry to cover completely.
(Leave stem exposed.)
Place on prepared baking sheet. Cover loosely and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Spread pecans on cookie sheet and dot with butter.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on paper towels to drain and lightly salt with regular or garlic salt while hot.
Cool and store in a vacuum container.

title: mexican rice
directions: Fry bacon.
Add onion, peppers, and ground beef.
Brown. Drain.
Add tomatoes, rice, chili powder, salt, and pepper.
Mix well and simmer covered for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed grilled quail or dove
directions: Lay breasts out flat.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder. Place 1 sliver jalapeno and a "dab" of cream cheese in the middle. Fold breast over.
Wrap 1/2 slice bacon around bird.
Secure with several toothpicks.
Cook on grill until done.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions; drain well. Saute celery and onion in 2 tablespoons butter until tender. Combine mixed vegetables, celery mixture, mayonnaise and cheese. Spoon into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons butter; sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: old fashioned raisin cake
directions: Combine.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Line oblong dish, 13 x 9 x 2 inch, with graham crackers, being careful to place graham crackers very close together.
Add powdered sugar to pudding mix.
Mix pudding, using only 3 cups milk for 2 packages of pudding.
Fold prepared whipped topping into pudding mixture until topping is completely blended.
Pour one-half of pudding mixture over graham crackers, slowly so as not to disturb cracker placement.
Add a layer of graham crackers, then spoon on other half of pudding mix, spreading it evenly over crackers.
Top with a solid layer of graham crackers.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil; boil 2 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour hot mixture over.
Mix well.
Drop onto waxed paper by spoonful.
Let stand until hard (about 1 hour).

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Chill for 24 hours if it lasts that long.
Serves 24.

title: fish in foil
directions: Place the fish on a 12 x 14-inch piece of foil.
Top with the onions, green peppers, lemons, parsley, paprika and white pepper. Sprinkle with the lemon juice.
Fold the foil into an envelope around the fish to seal in the juice.
Cook on an outdoor grill with the lid closed (or in a 450° oven) for 15 to 20 minutes or until the fish flakes easily with a fork.
Serves 1.

title: greek salad
directions: Combine everything together except white wine dressing.
Mix all ingredients, then add white wine dressing.
Add more than 1/2 cup if needed.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook until forms a soft ball in a cup of cold water.
Remove from heat; add 2 cups of quick cook oatmeal.
Drop with a spoon on wax paper.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and peppers together and drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients and place in a baking casserole dish. Bake at 325° for one hour, covered.
Serve with warm tortillas.

title: english muffin pizza
directions: Split muffins in half.
Place on cookie sheet.
Spread spaghetti sauce on each half.
Add the other topping on.
Put the cheese on last.
Broil in oven until cheese melts.
These are great for parties.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Brown pie shell lightly.
Mix chicken, vegetables, cream of chicken soup, chicken juice and potato.
Put layer of pie shell in casserole dish.
Pour in cooked vegetables.
Layer pie shell on top.
Put butter on top of pie shell and cook 30 minutes at 325°.

title: apple fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruits, except bananas, in large bowl.
Add pudding mix to reserved juices in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Mixture should be thick. Pour over fruits and chill.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: pink peppermint pie
directions: Over hot water, combine chocolate chips and milk; heat until chips melt and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; set aside. Over hot water, combine marshmallows, 1/2 cup of milk, salt, extract and food coloring; heat, stirring constantly until marshmallows melt and mixture is smooth.
Transfer to a large bowl and chill in refrigerator until slightly thickened (about 45 to 60 minutes).
Stir until smooth.
Gently fold in whipped cream. Spread half of the peppermint mixture into pie shell.
Dollop with half of the chocolate mixture.
With a knife, swirl chocolate mixture in a figure 8 pattern.
Repeat with remaining peppermint and chocolate mixtures.
Chill until firm.

title: smoked fish chowder
directions: Melt butter in large pot or soup kettle. Add chopped onion and fish cut into bite-size pieces. Saute lightly until onion is tender. Add potatoes and water. Cover and cook until potatoes are done. Add milk and warm just to boiling point. Garnish with parsley. Serve with whole wheat bread.
Flavor improves if leftover.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Will be thick.

title: orange kiss me cake
directions: Grind together orange (pulp and rind), 1 cup raisins and 1/3 cup walnuts.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and 1 cup sugar. Add shortening and 3/4 cup sour milk.
Beat for 2 minutes at low speed, then 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add 2 eggs (unbeaten) and 1/4 cup sour milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Fold orange/raisin mixture into batter.
Pour in oblong cake pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
After baking, while warm, drip 1/3 cup orange juice over cake.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Sprinkle over top of cake.
Add a few nuts for decoration.

title: semi-sweet frosted brownies for a crowd
directions: Melt 4 squares of chocolate, being careful not to burn.
Set aside to cool.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, to butter mixture, beating well after each.
Blend in cooled unsweetened chocolate and vanilla.

title: basic pastry
directions: Combine flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle water evenly over flour mixture.
Stir with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
(Do not overmix.) Form into ball.
May be refrigerated until ready for use.
Makes 9-inch pie.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and pat in pan.

title: low calorie dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Excellent with salads and as a dip.

title: crispy wings
directions: Cut up each wing into 3 sections.
Discard the end-bone portion.
Now each wing gives 2 pieces.
Marinate wings with salt and let it sit for 1 hour (overnight is okay too).
Turn stove to medium-high; on a nonstick pan, add 1/2 teaspoon oil.
Put chicken in and turn very frequently.
Do not cover pan.
Done in about 25 to 30 minutes, when wings are golden brown and crispy.
Most of the oil is squeezed out.
Drain and serve.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Mix all together and pour in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle top with dry yellow cake mix.
Slice margarine, thin, and lay on top of dry cake mix, side by side.
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: weight watchers ricotta omelette
directions: Beat egg, fold in Ricotta.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Cook in Teflon frypan.

title: beef over rice
directions: Saute ground beef and add salt.
Drain fat from meat and add 1 can of soup with 1 can milk.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 20 minutes.

title: white sauce for barbeque chicken
directions: Mix oil and sugar together.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well blended.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix dressing.
Pour over grated cabbage.
Mix well and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Melt butter.
Add flour, salt, dry mustard and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly for 2 minutes.
Do not brown.
Add milk, onion and Worcestershire sauce. Cook until smooth and thickened.
Stir in cheese until melted.

title: lasagne
directions: Dice sausages and brown, stirring often, in medium skillet. Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, onion and herbs.
Heat to boiling; simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend together eggs and sugar; blend until creamy.
Add peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: squash casserole 2
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into greased baking dish and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add sweet potatoes and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing 1 minute after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to potato mixture; stir well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours (use tube pan).
Ice cake while hot.

title: sour cream pastries
directions: Cut butter into flour to fine crumbs.
Combine egg yolk and sour cream; blend into flour mixture.
Chill dough several hours or overnight.
Divide dough into 4 equal portions, keeping each part refrigerated until ready to use.
Roll each part to 10-inch circle on lightly floured surface.
Spread with 2 tablespoons of the apricot preserves; sprinkle with 2 tablespoons coconut and 1 tablespoon nuts.
Cut each circle into 12 wedges with fluted pastry wheel.
Starting from wide end, roll each edge into a crescent.
Sprinkle with a little granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Remove from sheet; cool on rack.
Makes 4 dozen pastries.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Cream until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Add chopped apples and nuts (batter will be very stiff).
Spread batter evenly in a Bundt pan.
(If using a Teflon coated Bundt pan, spray lightly with vegetable spray.)
Bake at 325° for 1 hour (or until top of cake is golden brown and springs back when touched lightly).

title: herb crouton hot dish
directions: Layer hamburger, then croutons in casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soups and milk and pour over croutons.
Spread onions on top and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: chocolate heath bar cake
directions: Make 2 layers of cake (follow directions on cake box).
Make chocolate pudding as directed on box (Kahlua liquid optional). Refrigerate until firm; ready to use.
Crush 1 bag of Heath bars.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together; spread in a dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Put Cheddar cheese on top and bake another 15 minutes.
Serve with Triscuits crackers.

title: easy shortcake biscuits
directions: If you want plain biscuits, omit the sugar.

title: corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 9 x 9-inch pan.
In large mixing bowl, combine baking powder, salt, corn meal, sugar and flour. Stir well.
Add milk, egg and Crisco oil.
Stir.
Pour batter into greased pan and bake for 25 minutes.
Allow to cool for at least 10 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: italian potato cake for new years
directions: (Cook until tender - drain - mash them and let cool.)

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and crackers. Spread into pan or casserole dish. Sprinkle Ritz crackers on top; drizzle melted butter on top of crackers. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lynda's taco soup
directions: Brown meat with onions.
Drain off fat.
Mix together dry dressing and taco seasoning.
Mix into meat.
Then, without draining, mix in all other ingredients.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Soften tortillas in hot oil.
Spoon onto tortilla 2 tablespoons of the mixture and place on greased casserole pan (all of the ingredients can be mixed together).
The mixture that is left after filling the tortillas is poured over the top of the casserole to cover the entire surface.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together flour, oleo and 1 cup pecans and spread in pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

Then mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar together and spread on top of cool crust. Then mix pudding and milk and spread over creamed cheese mixture. Then spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: crab apple jelly
directions: To prepare juice, remove blossom and stem ends from about 3 1/2 pounds washed ripe crab apples.
Cut apples in small pieces. Do not peel or core.
Add 3 cups water; cover.
Simmer 10 minutes. Crush with masher.
Simmer, covered, 5 minutes (with soft, very sweet apples, add juice of 1 lemon to prepared juice before measuring).
Squeeze out juice.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt and Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shells.
Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients (except potatoes).
Cook very slow for 2 hours.
Add potatoes and cook until done.

title: down on the farm breakfast(microwave)
directions: Preparation:
Place chicken breasts between sheets of waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Pound slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a microwave-safe dish, melt butter and mix with oil. Place chicken breasts in dish, coating breasts on both sides. Microwave at High power for 3 minutes.
Let rest for 1 minute. Turn breasts over.
Microwave again at High power for 3 minutes until chicken breasts are done, not overcooked.
Set aside. Prepare sauce by mixing chives or green onion, lime juice and brandy, if used, mustard and parsley in a microwave-safe dish. Microwave at High power for 1 minute.
Add juices from chicken and broth.
Stir until smooth.
Pour sauce hot over chicken breasts. Serve immediately with noodles.

title: italian meatballs with herb sauce
directions: Combine meat, onions, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and egg; mix thoroughly.
Form into 12 (1 1/2-inch) balls.
Brown on all sides in oil.
Drain off fat.
Combine remaining ingredients except cornstarch and rice; blend until smooth over low heat in a small saucepan.
Pour over meatballs; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir 2 tablespoons water with cornstarch.
Pour into sauce; cook about 1 minute or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Serve over beds of fluffy rice.
Serves 6.

title: easy pecan dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in greased pie plate.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: Heat half the butter in a nonstick skillet until it bubbles. Add celery, onion, mushrooms and shrimp; saute only until the onion is clear and the celery a little pliable.
Add fish stock. Melt the other half of the butter in a 2-quart saucepan and stir in the flour to make a roux.
Add warm milk, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and is thoroughly blended.
Combine with the fish stock mixture, tomato puree and salt and pepper to taste. If too thick, a bit more milk and splash in sherry.
Serve hot.

title: chicken and broccoli with rice
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook and stir chicken in hot oil until slightly browned.
Stir in soup, milk, mustard and cheese; add broccoli and pimiento.
Bring to a full boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Pour over rice.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients well.
Pour over chicken. Cover with lid or foil. Bake 2 1/4 hours at 350°.
Do not peek!
Serves 4.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients very well.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Chill before serving.

title: rich silver cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Add 6 egg whites and beat 2 minutes more.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° in 2 round cake pans.

title: date-nut bars
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to eggs and beat.
Add dates, nut meats and vanilla.
Put in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and bake in 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 16 squares.

title: corn relish
directions: In a medium saucepan mix all ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to simmer. Cook about 5 mins. more. Pour in sterile jars and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: peach custard cake
directions: Mix like pie crust the flour, salt and margarine.
Press firmly on bottom
and halfway up sides of a 9 x 9-inch pan. Arrange drained peach slices on crust.
Sprinkle with a mixture of 1/2 cup of sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Pour salad oil into a medium saucepan.
Next, add onions and cook until light brown.
Add other ingredients and simmer 5 minutes.
Makes 2 cups of barbecue sauce.

title: pasta and broccoli
directions: In a six-quart pan, saute the garlic in oil at medium heat for one minute (not until golden).
In a separate pan, cook the broccoli in three quarts of water for 5 or 6 minutes.
Remove the broccoli from the water.
Take the water from the broccoli and pour it into the pan that has the garlic and olive oil.
Season the water with salt, pepper, garlic powder, parsley and oregano.
Put the broccoli in the pan and cook again at medium to low heat for 30 minutes.
At that point, start cooking the pasta in salted water in a separate pan.
Cook both for 15 minutes (the pasta will be al dente).
Drain the pasta.
Pour the broccoli and broth over the pasta and serve.
Serves eight.

title: puffed pancake with apples
directions: In a blender or large bowl, mix eggs, milk, flour, sugar, vanilla, salt and cinnamon until blended.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish in a preheated 425° oven.
Add apple slices to baking dish.
Return to oven until butter sizzles.
Do not let brown.
Remove dish from oven and immediately pour batter over apples.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake in middle of oven 20 minutes or until puffed and brown.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in 350 oven for 1 hour.
Do not wrap in foil. When done, cut in half and scoop out insides.
Whip potatoes and add sour cream, add egg and salt to taste.
Add cheese.
Fill potato halves with the mixture and sprinkle with paprika.
Put on tray and put in freezer.
To re-heat, bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: superb creamy dreamy chocolate fudge
directions: Melt butter or oleo and cheese and mix over low heat.
Stir in cocoa, sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Put in buttered pan.
Extra good recipe.

title: hot dogs 'n sauce
directions: Combine ketchup and sugar and cook 2 hours on low heat (simmer).
Then add bourbon and simmer another 1/2 hour.
Cut each hot dog into 4 pieces and put in sauce.
Heat in crock-pot for about 3 hours.
Start out on high and lower as it starts to bubble.

title: tourtiere
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in crust.
Make 5 small holes in top crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and 350° for 40 minutes.

title: curried hot fruit
directions: Butter 8 x 12-inch pan.
Add fruit.
Mix curry powder with brown sugar and sprinkle over fruit.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
The last 15 minutes sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons of tapioca to thicken.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together with a spoon the first 4 ingredients.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Blend two mixtures together well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit pies
directions: Mix lemon juice in milk.
Add to Cool Whip.
Drain pineapple and peaches, chopped up.
Add to Cool Whip mixture.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Makes 2 pies.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together as listed.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Blend butter, Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: honey-lime grilled chicken
directions: In a resealable plastic bag or shallow glass container, combine honey, soy sauce and lime juice.
Mix well.

title: peach-glazed fruit salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine pie filling, orange juice and lemon juice. Stir in the peaches, melon, grapes, apples and coconut. Cover and chill in the refrigerator 2 to 24 hours.
Makes 12 servings.

title: salmon spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and soup in microwave.
Heat and stir until smooth.
Dissolve gelatin in water and add soup mixture. Fold in remaining ingredients in a 5-cup mold.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheesecake fruit dip
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and milk until smooth. Fold in whipped topping and vanilla.
Makes 2 cups, 6 calories per teaspoon.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms of muffin cups.
Beat egg slightly with fork.
Stir in milk, pumpkin and shortening.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir in just until flour is moistened (batter should be lumpy).
Fold in raisins.
Fill cups 2/3 full. Sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon sugar over each muffin.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: country cabbage
directions: Spread 1/2 stick margarine in casserole dish.
Put cabbage in dish.
In a saucepan, mix milk, 1/2 stick margarine, flour, salt and pepper together.
Cook until it starts to bubble; remove from heat.
Add cheese.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix 1 sleeve Ritz crackers and the rest of the margarine together (more if needed). Spread on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5-inch pans. Combine 2 1/4 cups flour, sugar, poppy seed and baking powder in a bowl.
Beat in milk, oil and vanilla.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake until tester inserted comes out clean (50 to 60 minutes).
Serve warm or room temperature.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: dreamy spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed, then drain and cool.
Saute beef in butter, green pepper, onion and garlic until brown, then add tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat and cool. Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese and sour cream.

title: mustard vinaigrette salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender or processor.
Refrigerate. Makes 3/4 cup.

title: turkey supreme
directions: Saute onions and green peppers in oleo.
Add flour and stir until bubbly.
Add broth and milk.
Stir to thickened.
Add turkey and water chestnuts.
Stir until heated well.
Serve on toast or rice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini tarts
directions: Saute zucchini, onion and mushrooms in butter for about 5 minutes.
Add pinches of seasonings. Cool.

In bowl, beat cream cheese, milk, salt and egg until well mixed. Add a little cracked pepper. Combine sauteed vegetables into cream cheese mixture. Cook tart shells as directed (they come frozen, 8 to a package). Cool.
Just before serving, fill tart shells. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and bake at 375° to 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cracker stuffing
directions: Roll crackers real fine.
Mix sage in dry crackers.
Saute onions, celery and butter.
In a small pan, warm milk.
Beat eggs in a bowl.
Add onions, celery and butter to crackers.
Add eggs. Add milk, a little at a time, until crackers are real moist.

title: white cake icing
directions: Boil until it will spin a thread.
Beat egg whites stiff and add to boiled mixture. Beat until fluffy. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Make 2 layers in casserole of asparagus, small amount of asparagus juice, onion, salt, milk, soup and Cheese-Its.
Grated cheese may be sprinkled over top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: world's greatest apple pie
directions: I use Pillsbury pie crusts from the regular section of the grocery store.
Put them in your pie plate.
Combine all ingredients, mix together and put in pie shell.
Cover with top; make slits in top.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.
Place something under pie as it usually cooks over.

title: hot ham snacks
directions: Layer cheese, ham and cheese on hot dog bun and place in sheet cake pan. Slice into thirds. In saucepan, mix butter, mustard, Worcestershire, poppy seeds and dried onions. Spoon over buns. Cover with foil. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry meatloaf
directions: Spread sugar over bottom of greased loaf pan. Mash cranberry sauce and spread over sugar. Combine remaining ingredients, except for bay leaves. Shape into loaf and place on cranberry sauce. Place bay leaves on top of loaf. Bake at 350° about 1 hour. Remove bay leaves. Turn upside down and serve.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Blend in vanilla and rum extracts.
Sift flour with salt. Add alternately with sour cream, reserving 2 tablespoons of sour cream.
Blend soda into reserved sour cream and add to batter, stirring to blend.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: baked spaghetti and tomatoes
directions: Mix the spaghetti, tomato, salt, pepper and curry powder. Heat on surface burner until the mixture reaches boiling point. Cover and place in the oven, whose temperature is set at 250° or 275°.
Bake from 3 to 5 hours.
Then add the cheese and butter. Continue baking for 15 minutes longer.
Serve.

title: cracklin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add buttermilk and egg.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Whip eggs foamy. Add sugar, oil and zucchini. Stir well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into two loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour (greased and floured pans). After cooking for 1 hour, check and if not done, cook for 10 more minutes.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt into mixture.
Combine crumbled cornflakes, coconut and walnuts.
Mix into batter.
Roll cookie dough into small balls and bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie(mock pecan pie)
directions: Mix eggs, syrup, sugar and water.
Add margarine, coconut and oatmeal,
mixing well.
Pour into pie shell and bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: rye bread loaf and dip
directions: Mix all ingredients into bowl.
Cut
out top of 1 large loaf rye bread, leaving sides and bottom intact.
Pull remaining insides out of
loaf
in
bite-size
pieces.
Pour mixture into bread shell and
place
on
aluminum foil.
Put remaining bread pieces on foil around the
loaf
and
pull
foil
up and around bread.
Bake 30 minutes at
Take foil off top of loaf and bake 10 more minutes.

title: skillet spanish rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add onion, pepper, beef and rice.
Stir over high heat until slightly browned.
Add tomato sauce, water, salt and pepper.
Mix well and bring quickly to boil.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.

title: peasant salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix olive oil, vinegar, basil, capers, salt, pepper and garlic.
Cut tomatoes, cukes, yellow pepper and red onion into bite-size pieces.
Add vegetables to bowl with dressing; toss well.

title: pea picking cake
directions: Mix cake mix and vanilla pudding.
Add eggs, Crisco oil and mandarin oranges with juice.
Mix well.
Cook in layer or tube pan at about 325° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix peanut butter and melted butter together with a spoon. Add powdered sugar and knead with hands until smooth.

Roll into balls and dip in melted chocolate or put small amount of melted milk chocolate into bottom of peanut butter cup mold, then add a patty of peanut butter mixture and cover with more of the melted chocolate.
Put mold into freezer section of refrigerator for about 4 minutes, then turn mold over and tap finished candy onto table.

title: chocolate cake
directions: *To make buttermilk, add 1 teaspoon vinegar to sweet milk.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix in order down to coconut.
Pour in unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until done.
Top with meringue.
Sprinkle additional coconut on top.
Bake until meringue is light brown.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Cook beef, onion and green pepper together.
Drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients; cook 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Crumble bacon, blend in.

title: paintrock lodge good and moist chocolate cake
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients until dissolved and beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool, then frost with Paintrock Lodge Fluffy White Frosting.

title: strawberry ice cream for freezer
directions: Beat eggs until light, then beat in sugar. Add other ingredients and pour into freezer; freeze in 5-quart freezer.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Boil cornmeal, salt and water until thick and cool. Brown meat, onion and green pepper. Pour in tomatoes. Cook until mushy, about 1 hour. Add olives, chili powder and red and black pepper. Line deep pan with mush like pie crust; fill with meat mixture. Put mush crust on top. Add cheese. Bake until brown, approximately 45 minutes, at 375°.

title: cherry pretzel torte
directions: In medium
saucepan, melt butter.
Add sugar and blend. Remove from heat
and
stir
in
pretzel
crumbs.	Pat
in 9 x 13-inch baking
pan.
In
large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread mixture on crust. Cover with pie filling.
Chill 3 or 4 hours.

title: cauliflower-pea salad
directions: Cook peas until they are just thawed.
Cool.
Mix package of Ranch salad dressing mix and mayonnaise together.
Pour over cooled peas, cauliflower pieces and celery.
Mix well.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: a really good crust
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Beat egg, water and vinegar together.
Add flour mixture. Knead 20 times and chill.
Roll for 2 crusts.
This can also be frozen before rolling.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Blend ingredients and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake slowly at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: one skillet meal
directions: Lightly brown ground beef in an electric skillet.
Sprinkle shredded cabbage over the beef, then layer carrots, potatoes and onion.
Pour the two cans of soup over the mixture.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Turn skillet off.
Place cheese slices over mixture.
Cover with lid until cheese melts.
Keeps well in the freezer.

title: pastry crust
directions: Mix lightly.
Wrap and put in icebox for 30 minutes to a day. Form ball and place between 2 floured waxed papers.
Roll out quickly.
Put into sprayed pie pan.
Cover edges with foil.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Contains 54 calories and .13 gram fat.

title: banana split pie
directions: Cream together juice, cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 of Cool Whip, set aside.
Layer as follows:
place bananas in pie crust cover with crushed pineapple.
Top with cream mixture, then top with Cool Whip.
Top off with pecans and cherries.
Chill before serving.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Bone
chicken and line 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Mix soup and broth;
pour
over	chicken.
Slice
eggs
over
the soup mixture. Mix margarine, flour and milk to make a thin batter. Pour over top
of other mixture.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown (about 45 minutes).

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Pour on top of last layer.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes whole with skins on in salted water until not quite done.
Remove skins.
Grate coarsely on the large section of the grater.
Mix all other ingredients together, then add the grated potatoes.
Place mixture in large casserole dish.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350° or until hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: marshmallows
directions: Soak the gelatin in the cold water until it has taken up all the water.
Boil the sugar and water to the soft ball stage (238°).
Add vanilla and salt to gelatin.
Pour the syrup slowly over the gelatin, beating constantly with a whisk until cool and thick.

title: easy rouladan
directions: *I have used hamburger dill pickles.
This eliminates the cutting process.

title: good for the heart chicken curry
directions: In a large skillet, saute chicken, mushrooms and onions in oil until chicken is lightly browned on all sides.
Stir in flour, broth and curry powder.
Add apple and parsley, then pour milk and water.
Simmer, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes or until apple pieces are tender and crisp.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Calories per serving: 235 (or 335 with 1/2 cup rice).

title: chili beans
directions: When ground meat is almost done, add tomato paste, carrots, mushrooms, onions, tomatoes, celery and chili mix; bring to a boil.
Add chili powder, black pepper, Texas Pete and jalapeno peppers if you wish.
Mix with beans; bring to a boil. Turn on low heat and simmer 10 minutes. Ready to eat. Enjoy!

title: b. j.'s fruit salad
directions: Empty pudding into bowl.
Mix juices together and use quantity as required on pudding package (in place of milk).
Mix pudding and juices together and add fruit.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients; melt butter (or margarine).
Add sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, chocolate chips and nuts. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven when soft.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook diced eggplant.
Drain.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add flour to thicken.
Stir in tomatoes and brown sugar.
Pour over eggplant and put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: 13 bean soup
directions: *Types of beans used:
Limas (baby, large, green and speckled), peas (black-eyed and split), lentils and beans (pink, kidney, black, navy, Great Northern and garbanzo).

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into an 8 or 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or longer.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix ingredients for salad dressing and add pears and red onion.
Add to bowl and chill covered for one hour.
Just before serving.
mix in 1 pound washed baby spinach leaves.

title: chocolate crackles
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
Combine well with brown sugar and oil. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Add nuts.
Chill dough.
(Best when chilled overnight.)

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and cinnamon with fork until crumbly. Put pie filling in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Spread cake mixture over pie filling.
Bake about 350° to 400° for about 15 to 20 minutes until brown (don't overcook).

title: lori's baked spaghetti
directions: Boil spaghetti as directed on package.
Brown ground beef; drain, mix with sauce and a little of the shredded mozzarella cheese.
Mix spaghetti with the sauce mixture and pour into a greased 9 x 13 inch or 11 x 13 inch pan and top with remaining cheese.
You can also sprinkle some Parmesan cheese on top.

title: spicy mediterranean meatballs
directions: Crumble meat into a large bowl.
Add bread crumbs, eggs and onion; mix well.
Sprinkle with parsley, mint, paprika, salt, pepper and cloves.
Mix lightly until well combined.
Shape into 1-inch balls.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine first 5 ingredients.
Top with crackers and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: 7-up jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Blend sugar and cream cheese. Add to jello. Blend and cool. Add pineapple, vanilla and 7-Up. Refrigerate until set.

title: ten thousand chocolate cookies
directions: Get the biggest mixing bowl you can find anywhere in Clarendon County.
Cream butter, sugar and shortening.
Sift dry ingredients together.
By this time, you will have to move out of the kitchen.
Don't get discouraged, there are lots of other recipes that are easier to make and oh! so good!

title: apple cake
directions: Combine cake mix with butter until crumbly.
Remove 2/3 cup for topping and add brown sugar and cinnamon to it.
Mix well and set aside.
Press remaining mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased). Arrange peeled, sliced apples on top.
Blend sour cream and egg and spread on apples.
Sprinkle with reserved topping.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.
Refrigerate any left overs.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Put in milk, flour, butter and salt. Mix.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: sid's favorite mexican dip
directions: *Could use a can of refried beans with hot jalapeno salsa to taste.

title: oreo cake
directions: Break cookies up and pour stick of butter over them.
Beat cream cheese and 1/2 container of Cool Whip together.
Pour over cookies.
Mix vanilla and chocolate pudding together, put on top of Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Apply rest of Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Keep refrigerated.

title: hot chicken wings
directions: Cut wings in half; marinate 1 hour in vinegar, oil and hot sauce.
Remove from marinade and drain.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: potato cakes(bleenies)
directions: Peel, wash and grate the potatoes and onion into a large bowl. Add egg and flour; mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: stir-fry noodles
directions: Place 2 cups of water in a pan and bring to a boil.
Add noodles to water, reserving seasoning packet.
Cook until done, then drain water and set aside, covered.

title: st. paul's casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain grease off well.
Mix soup, water and rice together.
Bring to a boil and boil for 7 minutes.
Dice pepper, celery and onion.
Add all together and put into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook and crumble bacon.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate until served.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Drop in chicken a few pieces at a time.
Shake to coat.
Heat oil 1/4-inch deep in a 12-inch or electric skillet to 350°.
Fry chicken skin-side down, 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn; fry 15 to 20 minutes longer until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Chop shrimp coarsely.
Combine all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Fold in shrimp.
Chill overnight.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: potato cakes
directions: Melt shortening in an iron skillet.
Mix the potatoes, egg and flour. Shape into balls.
Place in hot shortening.
Flatten with a spatula and fry on both sides until brown.
For extra flavor, add 1 tablespoon minced onion to the potatoes and flour.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: In small bowl, combine walnuts, cinnamon and 3/4 cup sugar. Grease 10-inch tube pan.
In large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine or butter with 1 1/4 cups sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour and remaining ingredients and beat at low speed until blended, constantly scraping bowl with rubber spatula. Increase speed to medium, beat 3 minutes, scraping bowl.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread half of batter in pan.
Sprinkle with half of nut mixture.
Spread evenly with remaining batter and sprinkle with remaining nut mixture.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes until cake pulls away from side of pan.
Cool cake in pan completely on wire rack.

title: holiday truffles
directions: Melt chocolate chips in medium saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in orange liqueur and frosting, blending well.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours, until firm. Place coconut on wax paper or plate.
Scoop mixture into 1-inch balls and drop into coconut; roll to coat.
Place in foil or paper candy cups, if desired.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 6 dozen candies.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown
the
hamburger
and
sausage; drain well and set aside. Combine
all
the	remaining
ingredients,
except the chips.
In a
large,
nonstick pan, place on low heat and stir until the cheese is melted and mixture is thoroughly hot.
Add the sausage and hamburger.
Mix well and pour the hot mixture in a crock
pot to	keep hot.
Serve with corn chips for dipping.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Put 4 slices of bacon in cold skillet and fry until brown. Remove bacon from pan and set aside to cool.
To the skillet, add the onion and saute for a few minutes.
Next add vinegar, sugar, then cornstarch, mixed with the water, and salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling and remove from heat.
Add drained green beans and toss lightly together.
Pour beans in dish; crumble bacon and sprinkle on top.

title: taco rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients except tortillas and spread on tortillas.
Slice.
Serve with salsa.

title: broiled sandwiches
directions: Spread mayonnaise on the bread and place on a baking sheet covered with aluminum foil and sprayed with Pam.
