Add ingredients in the order listed.
Broil until the bacon is sizzling and crisp. Watch closely to be sure the cheese does not burn.
Serves 4.

title: barbecues
directions: Brown peppers and onions.
Add the rest and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: chicken-wild rice salad
directions: Combine chicken, pineapple and rice in large bowl.
Whisk together vinegar, oil, salt and curry powder in small bowl. Combine with chicken mixture.
Chill for 3 hours.
Add remaining ingredients to chicken mixture.
Toss gently.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chef tell's spinach stuffed pork chops
directions: In an all-purpose casserole, combine spinach and water; cover. Place on Micro-Go-Round in microwave oven.
Microwave at High for 5 to 6 minutes, breaking up spinach frequently.
Drain spinach; remove from casserole.
Place 2 tablespoons butter in casserole. Microwave uncovered at High for 30 seconds, or until butter melts. Add anchovies; microwave at High for 1 minute.
Stir in spinach, salt and pepper.
Microwave at High for 2 or 2 1/2 minutes or until heated through.
Remove spinach mixture from casserole; set aside.

title: carameled popcorn
directions: Boil for 5 minutes, pour over popcorn.

title: good chocolate sheet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture with buttermilk.
Make a paste of boiling water and cocoa. When cool, add to batter.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: browned rice
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart casserole.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add rice, water and bouillon cubes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi and capellini
directions: Devein shrimp.
Add finely chopped garlic and 2 sticks of butter in a medium saucepan on low flame.
Stir frequently.
When butter is melted, add white wine and lemon juice.
Stir together. Add spices (garlic powder, salt, parsley).
Cook approximately 1/2 hour on low flame.
Toss over capellini.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Keeps indefinitely stored in refrigerator.
Serve with raw vegetables or chips.

title: coley's chicken curry spread
directions: Mix together and chill for about an hour.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix the cake mix as directed.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch pan (greased and floured).
On top of cake batter, spread the rhubarb. Sprinkle the sugar over that, then pour the half and half.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: granola
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly, add oil and mix thoroughly again.
Heat honey until it flows freely and add with molasses to ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 275° in a large broiler or pans without cover for 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 15 to 20 minutes to toast evenly.
Color should be light brown.
Bake on shelf 3 inches above coils.
Yields 26 cups, or 7 1/2 pounds.
Can be used as breakfast cereal, on hot cereals and as a snack.

title: broccoli delight
directions: Break broccoli into bite size pieces.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill 3 hours before serving.

title: potato risotto
directions: Blanch potatoes by boiling for 7 minutes; drain and set aside.
Saute shallots in olive oil over medium heat, 3 minutes or until soft.
Add cream and boil until mixture thickens and is reduced by 1/4.
Stir in cheese, potatoes, pepper and salt.

title: gator gravy
directions: Fry bacon crisp; add celery, green peppers and onions.
Cook until tender. Add flour and brown. Add enough water to make adequate gravy. Pour in tomatoes and season to taste.
Simmer 30 minutes. Great over grits at a fish fry.

title: cream cheese pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with cooking spray.
Spread 1 package of cookie dough in bottom of pan.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Beat softened cream cheese until creamy.
Add condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Set aside.
Then mix instant pudding and milk as directed on box.
Mix pudding with cream cheese mixture.

title: parsley rice ring
directions: Combine hot, cooked rice with parsley.
Pack into an ungreased 5 1/2-cup ring mold.
Turn out at once on a warm platter.
Serves 6.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, combine broccoli, onion and water. Microwave, covered, on High for 4 to 5 minutes.
In a food processor bowl, combine cooked broccoli mixture, lemon juice, horseradish, salt and pepper. Cover and blend until smooth.
In a 1-quart casserole, gradually stir broccoli mixture into softened cheese. Stir in the milk and hot sauce.
Microwave, uncovered, 12 minutes on High, stirring once.
Serve with vegetable dippers.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and apples.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch morsels over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Beat eggs well, adding sugar and Crisco.
Add everything else. Work with hands or if strong enough, use wooden spoon!
Cook in well-greased and floured angel or spring-form pan.
Cook at 350° about 1 hour or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: slight pudding
directions: Thicken milk with flour and butter.
Cook this in a double boiler until it begins to thicken, then remove and begin to cool. While this is cooling, beat the yolks with a teacup of sugar and add to it.
Then beat the egg whites to a stiff froth and stir in lightly.
Bake to a light brown at 250°.
Flavor with lemon.

title: lois's family jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in egg yolks, one at a time. Mix well. Stir in jam. Add flour and spices-that have been sifted together three times-alternate with sour cream, ending with flour. Fold in egg whites that have been beaten to stage where peaks stand firm. Bake in 4-9 inch layers in moderate oven at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and cream together with margarine and sugar.
Add syrup, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 400° for ten minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes more.

title: english creek pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
Sear pork chops on both sides until browned.
If you want, you can put onion on top of pork chops or you can leave plain.
Combine ketchup, beer and brown sugar.
Pour over pork chops.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 1 hour.
The longer they simmer the better.
Serve by spooning sauce over each pork chop.

title: crab spread
directions: Heat cream of mushroom soup.
Mix together gelatin and water; add to soup.
Mix together mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Add to soup.
Add celery, onions and crab meat to mixture.
Put in a 6-cup mold.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours.

title: polish kraut and apples
directions: Place half of the sauerkraut in an ungreased slow cooker. Top with sausage, apples, brown sugar, caraway seeds, if desired, and pepper. Top with remaining sauerkraut. Pour apple juice over all. Cover and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours or until apples are tender.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Heat some olive oil in large frypan.
Saute garlic and onion until tender.
Add tomato and pepper and saute a few minutes longer on medium-low heat.
Remove from pan and reserve juice and all. If necessary, add more oil to pan.
Add chicken, salt and pepper; saute until cooked through and golden brown.
Add vegetable mixture back to pan.
Stir together with chicken and heat through. Serve with rice.

title: biscotti
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine sugar, baking powder and butter.
Blend in the extract.
Add the eggs one at a time.
Add the flour 1 cup at a time.
Spoon the dough onto a greased cookie sheet to form 2 logs, 1 1/2 inches wide by 1 inch high.
To shape the logs, wet your hands and pat the top and sides of the dough. Brush the logs with egg wash and bake 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball or log
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Shape into logs or balls. Roll into chopped nuts.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix together well; place in a casserole and bake 30 or 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large mixing bowl, combine pumpkin, condensed milk, eggs and cinnamon.
Blend well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 15 minutes, then reduce oven temperature to 350°. Bake 35 to 40 minutes longer until center of pie is set.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix first six ingredients and bring to a boil.
Set aside to cool.
Finely chop cabbage, peppers, carrot and onion.
Mix vegetables together and pour the cooled vinegar mixture over them. Place in containers and freeze.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt the first 3
ingredients in a large measuring cup in the microwave.
Stir well the Corn Chex and powdered sugar. Pour cereal in a large roasting pan.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal and toss well.
Place sugar in a brown paper bag and add cereal mixture.
Fold down bag; take outside and shake well. Remove from bag and allow to "dry" on cookie sheets.
Store in airtight container.

title: greek-style lamb and lentil stew
directions: Arrange the lamb cubes in a single layer in a shallow ovenproof dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 400° oven, about 25 minutes, turning occasionally, until cubes are browned.
Drain and discard any fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 servings, 225 calories each.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls in large cookie sheet to form crust. Follow baking time on package.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese and Ranch dressing together.
Spread on crust when cool and add vegetable toppings.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Mix and heat to almost boiling the margarine, cocoa and buttermilk.
Add sugar.
Beat until smooth.

title: pineapple texas sheet cake
directions: Melt oleo; add cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla. Stir.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Place cooked turkey or chicken in bottom of an 8 x 11-inch casserole dish. Cover with Swiss cheese slices. Combine soup and water; pour over turkey. Top with the dry stuffing (mixed with the flavor packet). Pour melted margarine over top. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: danish(diabetic recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
On nonstick baking sheet, bake biscuits for 3 minutes.
Remove biscuits from oven and, using metal 1 teaspoon measure, make an indentation in center of each.
Fill each indentation with 1 teaspoon raspberry spread.
Return biscuits to oven and bake until golden brown, 3 to 4 minutes. Sprinkle raspberry portion of each danish with 1/2 teaspoon coconut.
Let cool.
Serve warm.
Makes 2 servings.
One danish equals 1 bread and 1/2 fat.

title: potato dumplings for stew
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls on top of hot stew.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 dumplings.

title: people chow
directions: Combine cereal, pretzels and peanuts.
Melt chocolate chips; pour over cereal mixture.
Toss to coat.
Spread in a greased cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: guacamole no. 2
directions: Place first six ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Fold in chopped tomato and green onions.
Makes approximately 2 cups.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° until done.

title: eggplant manicotti
directions: Peel eggplant, cut in half lengthwise.
Slice into thin long slices (1/8-inch thick).
In heavy skillet, saute each slice in olive oil over medium heat, turning only once and cooking just until eggplant becomes limp enough to roll.
Cool and drain slices on paper towel.
Combine the remaining ingredients, except tomato sauce.
Spread each eggplant slice with a thin layer of cheese mixture.
Roll each slice and place seam side down in buttered casserole dish.
Pour tomato sauce over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: old time chocolate peppermint cake
directions: Beat butter, eggs, sugar, and vanilla on high speed for 3 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and stir gently until combined. Pour into two 8 inch pans that have been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
For the crumb mixture, crush corn flakes finely enough to make 1 cup of crumbs or use 1/2 cup bread crumbs; set aside.
Rinse chicken pieces; pat dry with paper toweling. Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Brush each piece with melted butter.
Place crushed corn flakes or bread crumbs on a sheet of waxed paper; roll chicken in crumbs to coat.
Arrange chicken, skin side up and not touching in a shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 50 minutes or until tender.
Do not turn.
(Chicken is done when it is easily pierced with a fork.
Test the thigh or breast at a point near the bone, since these parts require the most cooking time.)
Makes 6 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need clay pot, flower and trowel.

title: twice-baked sweet potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Bake until tender.
Cut in half lengthwise. Scoop out insides, leaving shell.
Mash scooped out potato, mix in syrup, butter, cinnamon, ginger and 2 tablespoons pecans.
Re-stuff potato shells with mixture.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with the rest of the nuts and drizzle more syrup over potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: pennywise steak
directions: Mix lean ground beef with onion, mustard, milk, parsley, salt, and pepper.
Spread thinly on cut halves of rolls overlapping a little down the sides to allow for shrinkage.
Broil till top is nice and brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cook
syrup
and
sugar until mixture thickens, about 5 minutes.
Beat eggs well.
Add hot syrup slowly while continuing to	beat.
Add butter and vanilla.	Pour into unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle
in the nuts.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes, then in a slow oven (300°) for about 35 more minutes. Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: johnny apple chops
directions: Arrange chops in a single layer in shallow baking dish with meatiest portion toward outside edges.
Top with lemon slices. Add 2/3 cup apple juice and 1/3 cup water.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Reduce power to Medium; microwave 15 to 18 minutes.
Let stand, covered, while preparing gravy.
Pour 1 cup pan juices into 2 cup glass measure; discard remaining juices.

title: pepper steak
directions: Slice meat very thin across grain.
Cook in oil until loses pink.
Add water, onion and garlic.
Simmer 40 minutes.
Add bell peppers; cook 5 minutes.
Blanch tomatoes in boiling water.
Remove skin; quarter.
Mix starch, sugar, soy and add to meat.
Simmer 1 minute.
Add tomatoes.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: double berry coco punch
directions: Prepare Ice Ring in advance, if desired.
In blender container, puree strawberries and cream of coconut until smooth. In a large punch bowl, combine strawberry mixture and cranberry juice. Just before serving, add club soda and Ice Ring.
Makes about 4 quarts.

title: red wine sauce for steak
directions: Heat butter and wine.
Add green onions and parsley.
Heat and pour over steak.

title: dilly cabbage
directions: Saute cabbage and onion in bacon grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer until tender.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend in sugar, oleo, and milk.
Pour over pineapple cubes.
Bake covered in ungreased 9 x 13 pan or 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish at 350°.
Excellent side dish for ham or turkey.

title: stuffed mushroom
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms. Cook caps in butter/margarine for 4 to 5 minutes. Combine ingredients and fill caps. Broil until golden brown.

title: holiday quiche
directions: Combine cheese and flour. Sprinkle over pie shell.
Mix remaining ingredients, beating until smooth.
Pour over cheese in pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Garnish with parsley and pimento before serving.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, egg yolks and lemon juice well.
Pour into crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then add 3 teaspoons sugar to each egg white.
I add cream (1/2 spoon) before I beat the egg whites.
Add to top of pie.
Good luck.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix ingredients, pour in 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: kids popcorn cake
directions: Melt butter, oil and marshmallows.
Add pecans after mixture has cooled some.
Add popcorn and gumdrops.
Mix with hands. Press into a greased angel food pan.
Let cool and put on plate.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Heat milk, margarine and cheese until melted.
Pour over top of thawed hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: del rio dip
directions: Mix together.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add garlic powder to taste.
Let chill overnight or several hours before serving.
Serve with Doritos or Tostitos.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: easy cheese souffle
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Blend butter and cheese spread.
Cut crust from bread.
Spread cheese mixture on one side of bread; place cheese side down in pan.
Spread cheese mixture on other side of bread.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Make a roux (gravy) with oleo and flour in large kettle. Cook, stirring constantly, until a rich brown.
Stir in onions and garlic; cook, stirring often, until soft, about 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, chicken broth, water, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper seasoning.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and fish flakes. Continue cooking until shrimp turns pink (no more than 10 to 12 minutes).
Stir in filet powder (always last) to thicken.
Serve over rice.
Makes 8 servings.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as on box.
Pour into 12 x 15 x 2-inch pan. Only grease bottom.
Mix cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Pour on top of cake mix and spread out.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake in oven at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: mary holland's vegetable casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.
Layer vegetables in dish with bread crumbs in between layers.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chow mein candy
directions: Melt morsels.
Stir in all other ingredients, then spread on wax paper and cool.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Mix well. This will be thick. Spray cookie sheet with Pam. Spread mixture on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin. Add sifted dry ingredients. Add nuts and pie filling. Bake in 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°. (Check after 1 hour.*)

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash cucumbers about 6 inches long (as long as they are firm and fresh); leave whole and fill gallon jars.
Pour unsalted boiling water over to cover; weight down with a cup or something. Each morning, pour liquid off into kettle and heat to boiling and pour back over cucumbers for four days.

title: hash brown dish
directions: Put all together in a baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350°. You may use 2 cups of potato chips or cornflakes and 1/4 cup margarine with flakes for top the last 20 minutes of baking.

title: gram norman's lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream together sugar, butter, salt and flour.
Add and beat lemon juice and rind, egg yolks.
Add milk to mixture and beat again.
Fold in stiffly beaten whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: church chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in shallow roasting pan.
Place slice of ham on top of each piece of chicken.
Whip together soup and sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 250° for 3 hours.

title: kathy's raw apple cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs.
Use ungreased floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: oat bran and raisin muffins or cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Add raisins last. Makes 12 muffins.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: white chip orange dream cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt in a small bowl.
Beat butter and sugars in large bowl until creamy.
Beat in egg and orange peel. Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in morsels.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are light golden brown. Let stand 2 minutes; remove to wire racks to cool completely.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, soup and chicken broth together in a pot. Warm on stove.
Boil and debone chicken.
Cut into chunks.
Melt a stick of butter in casserole dish.
Crumble crackers in the bottom to mix with the butter.
This serves as a crust.
Add chicken on top of crackers.
Pour soup mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: chocolate roll-up
directions: Beat whites, cream of tartar and vanilla until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Sift remaining ingredients; fold into yolks until blended.
Fold yolks into whites.
Line a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan with waxed paper; grease.
Spread batter in pan. Bake in slow oven (325°) for about 25 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Layer first three ingredients in a gallon jar.
Mix last five ingredients well.
Heat until sugar is melted, then pour over pickles in jar.
Store in refrigerator.
Ready to eat after 3 days.

title: best ever sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes.
Boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Allow potatoes to cool to touch; peel and slice. Arrange slices in a lightly greased 3-quart baking dish.
Pour orange juice mixture over potatoes and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate or coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add egg yolks.
Add cream and water.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
If making coconut pie, add coconut when you add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Use Cool Whip or make meringue.

title: angela's popcorn cake
directions: Pop the corn.
Melt margarine.
Add marshmallows; stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour over popcorn; mix well and press in angel food cake pan.
When cool, you can decorate with candies.

title: savory lentil pot pie
directions: Cook onion, carrots and celery in water with broth until about half done.
Add potatoes.
Brown flour in frying pan and blend with margarine.
Add 1 cup hot liquids from vegetables.
Cook until thickened and combine with rest of vegetable mixture.
Add lentils, sage, parsley and salt.
Consistency should be thin.
Place in a large casserole or baking pan and cover with pie crust.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown.

title: pappa's ice cream
directions: Mix well; pour into ice cream freezer.
Freeze.
Very delicious.

title: church supper casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease two 9 x 13-inch pans. Heat cooking oil and onion, green peppers and garlic in very large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Add ground beef.
Keep cooking until browned.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into prepared baking dishes.
Cover and bake about 45 minutes.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 15 minutes more.
Makes about 20 servings.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Cook beef and onion until tender and brown. Drain. Add spices to suit taste.
Mix together Ro-Tel chilies and tomatoes with soup and the two cheeses.
Heat until smooth.
Layer in casserole dish 1/2 tortillas, beef, beans and cream mixture, then layer again.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix sugar, strawberry jello and crushed pineapple; bring to a boil.
Cool real good (cold).
Add Cool Whip, pecans and coconut. Pour into mold and refrigerate.
(Can be frozen.)
Holds up good out of refrigerator.

title: green eggs and ham
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine in skillet over medium heat.
Beat eggs and add ham.
When onion and pepper is soft, add egg and ham mixture and scramble.

title: strawberry tapioca
directions: Heat water.
Add sugar and salt. Bring to a boil and add tapioca and simmer about 5 to 10 minutes until tapioca is clear. Immediately add Jell-O.
Frozen strawberries can be put in while hot to melt.
Cool before adding fresh strawberries.

title: cheese cake
directions: Melt butter.
Use 2 tablespoons to grease 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat 8 ounces cream cheese until creamy.
Beat in 2 eggs. Add cream cheeses and eggs until all are finished.
Add sour cream, sugar and cream all together.
Add cornstarch, vanilla and remaining butter.
Beat until very smooth and creamy.

title: coconut upside-down cake
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Sprinkle brown sugar over margarine.
Arrange pineapple slices over sugar mixture, filling center with cherries and filling in between circles of fruit with pecans.
Sprinkle coconut over all.
Pour cake batter over all. Bake in a 10-inch heavy skillet at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zesty shrimp sauce with linguine
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over medium heat.
Add olive oil.
Saute onion, peppers and garlic.
Add salsa, lime juice and shrimp.
Cook until shrimp turn pink, 5 to 8 minutes, depending on size of shrimp.

title: vidalia onion spread
directions: Combine and heat in microwave until hot and cheese melts.

title: cheese rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Make balls and brown on medium heat.
Drain after browning. Place back in skillet.
Add 2 cups mushroom soup to make sauce. Simmer until thickened.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa.
Add milk and Karo syrup.
Cook over low flame until small amount dropped in cold water forms a soft ball, approximately 29 minutes.

title: toasted clam and cheese appetizers
directions: Mix clams, cheese and mayonnaise in a large bowl.
Spread onto slices of bread.
Put in 350° oven until cheese is melted (about 10 minutes).

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Fry ground beef.
Cut tops off peppers and remove insides. Place peppers in boiling water to parboil (2 minutes).
Drain and cool.
Mix ground beef with first 5 ingredients.
Mix well and fill pepper cavities.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Place 1/2 c. boiling water in bottom of pan while peppers are cooking.

title: shrimp avocado salad
directions: Combine shrimp and next 7 ingredients.
Combine mayonnaise, catsup and paprika; mix well.
Line 4 individual salad bowls with lettuce leaves.
Fill with shrimp mixture.
Pour desired amount of dressing on top.
Garnish with egg slices, olives and tomato.

title: jello fluff
directions: In saucepan put the water and sugar; stir until dissolved. Bring to boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add dry jello.
Set aside.
Pour evaporated milk in mixing bowl and beat with mixer until stiff peaks form.
Slowly pour jello mixture into milk.
(Do not use mixer, fold mixtures together by hand.) Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top and refrigerate for a couple of hours.

title: oven fried chicken pieces
directions: Set oven to 375°.
Place margarine in a shallow baking pan. Place in oven for 3 to 4 minutes or until margarine melts.

title: chocolate lassies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Mix and sift flour, baking soda and spices; add.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: creamy waldorf salad
directions: Core and dice apples; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add celery and grapes to apples and toss.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar, and cream. Pour over apple mixture and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Just before serving add nuts and toss to mix.

title: grandma englehaupt's sugar cookies
directions: Mix all of ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon onto coated cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar and margarine.
Beat the eggs and add to sugar mix.
Add soda, milk to mix.
Sift together 1 teaspoon allspice and 1 cup flour and add to mixture.
Add pecan halves, dates-chopped.
Chop candied fruit and coat with 1/2 cup flour. Mix all ingredients and add 4 tablespoons whiskey.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 about 20 minutes.

title: chicken headcheese
directions: Debone chicken legs; cut meat in small pieces.
Boil the chicken with water, spices and onion until thick.
Soften gelatine in a small amount of water; add to mixture.
Let thicken and refrigerate.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine for 1 minute (or a little longer if necessary).
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, uncooked oatmeal and vanilla.
Mix well and drop spoonfuls on waxed paper to cool.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Combine together 3 1/2 cups flour, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, allspice and salt in bowl.
Beat together egg, sugar, molasses and oil.
Add 1 cup flour to egg, sugar, molasses and oil mixture and then add cold water and vinegar.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake in rectangular pan. When cool, cut cake in half like 2 layers. Mix vanilla pudding; spread on first layer, then place sliced strawberries on that. Put other layer on top of berries. Put whipped cream or Cool Whip on top of that. Put strawberries and glaze on top of that. Keep in refrigerator. Very good.

title: barbecue sauce for salmon
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add other ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Place salmon pieces on barbecue, skin side down.
Brush sauce on salmon and cover with foil.
Baste often. Cook until fish flakes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Combine pineapple and marshmallows and refrigerate overnight. Add chopped nuts and small carton of cream (whipped).

title: brie quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prick pastry shell and bake 12 minutes. Remove and reduce temperature to 375°.
Blend Brie, cream cheese, butter and cream.
Add eggs and blend well.
Season with Tabasco. Stir in chives.
Pour into pastry shell and set in upper third of oven.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until quiche has puffed and top is brown.

title: nutty green beans(microwave)
directions: Wash beans; remove strings.
Cut beans into 1-inch pieces. Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add water; cover and microwave at High 16 to 17 minutes, or until crisp-tender.
Drain; keep warm.
Place butter in a pie plate.
Microwave at High 50 seconds, or until melted.
Add pecans and remaining ingredients; microwave at High 2 to 3 minutes, or until onion is tender, stirring after each minute.
Pour butter mixture over beans, tossing to coat. Yields 4 servings.

title: egg casserole
directions: The day before, butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat milk and egg together.
Put in layers bread, cheese, ham, milk and egg mixture. Put in refrigerator overnight covered with foil.
Bake covered at 325° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: oreo and cream delight
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix with Oreo crumbs.
Mix ice cream and Cool Whip.
Pour in crumbs and mix well.
Freeze before serving.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine eggs, salt and milk; add flour.
Mix all together. Roll out thin (really thin).
Cut into thin strips and let dry. Cook, uncovered, for about 10 minutes.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: In a bowl, stir together cream cheese, garlic salt, pepper and sour cream until smooth.
Set aside.
Prepare and boil quartered potatoes.
Drain.
Using an electric mixer or a potato masher, beat hot potatoes until they are in fine lumps.
Add sour cream mixture and continue beating until fluffy and smooth.

title: creamsicle dessert
directions: Break cake into small pieces. Fill buttered 9 X 13 pan with cake pieces. Dissolve jello in hot water, add sherbet and stir. Allow to thicken slightly. Fold in whipped cream. Pour over cake pieces and refrigerate. Top with additional whipped cream and mandarin oranges slices if desired.

title: chocolate-filled oatmeal bars
directions: Cream margarine, brown sugar and salt.
Blend in flour and oatmeal until crumbly.
Press 2/3 of the mixture into the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and stir in nuts.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/3 crumb mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: olive spread
directions: Mix together.
Pour into glass pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until brown.
Serve with Triscuits/crackers, etc.

title: chile con chips
directions: Combine ingredients and warm over low heat just to bubbling. Remove from heat.
Either pour over tortilla strips and sprinkle with remaining grated cheese for nachos, or pour into serving bowl, sprinkle with the remaining cheese and serve with tortilla strips for dipping.
Easy and delicious!

title: baked carrots
directions: Arrange carrots in 1-quart buttered casserole.
Pour remaining ingredients over carrots.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pheasants with brandy and cream
directions: Saute shallots in butter.
Add pheasants and saute until brown.
Pour brandy into ladle and remainder over pheasants, flame. Add bouillon, salt and pepper.
Arrange bacon over top and roast, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes, basting frequently.
Stir cream and horseradish into juices, continue roasting 15 minutes more, basting frequently.
Serve with wild rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together in blender.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake for about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: summer vegetable salad
directions: In bowl, combine vegetables and cheese.
Whisk together remaining ingredients. Pour over the vegetables.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pineapple dream bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium mixer bowl, beat butter and 1/3 cup brown sugar.
Blend in 1 cup flour until mixture is crumbly.
Pat onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated oven 10 to 15 minutes or until golden.
Keep oven hot, but remove pan to cool.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix as directed on box.
Pour 1/2 of cake mix in pan, then half brown sugar mixture, then add remainder of cake mix.
Top with remainder of brown sugar mixture; swirl with knife.
Bake at 275° for 15 minutes, then 25 minutes at 300°.

title: wonderful pot roast
directions: Combine flour and pepper; coat pot roast.
In Dutch oven, brown roast in oil; drain.
Add water, tomatoes, caraway seed, onion soup mix and bay leaves
Bring to boil.
Reduce to heat; cover tightly and simmer 2 to 3 hours, or until roast is tender. Makes 6 to 8 servings.
